name: java.applet
description: Provides the classes necessary to create an applet and the classes an applet uses to communicate with its applet context.

Interface Summary.name: AppletContext
Interface Summary.description: This interface corresponds to an applet's environment: the document containing the applet and the other applets in the same document.

Interface Summary.name: AppletStub
Interface Summary.description: When an applet is first created, an applet stub is attached to it using the applet's setStub method.

Interface Summary.name: AudioClip
Interface Summary.description: The AudioClip interface is a simple abstraction for playing a sound clip.

Class Summary.name: Applet
Class Summary.description: An applet is a small program that is intended not to be run on its own, but rather to be embedded inside another application.

name: java.awt
description: Contains all of the classes for creating user interfaces and for painting graphics and images.

Interface Summary.name: ActiveEvent
Interface Summary.description: An interface for events that know how to dispatch themselves.

Interface Summary.name: Adjustable
Interface Summary.description: The interface for objects which have an adjustable numeric value contained within a bounded range of values.

Interface Summary.name: Composite
Interface Summary.description: The Composite interface, along with CompositeContext, defines the methods to compose a draw primitive with the underlying graphics area.

Interface Summary.name: CompositeContext
Interface Summary.description: The CompositeContext interface defines the encapsulated and optimized environment for a compositing operation.

Interface Summary.name: ItemSelectable
Interface Summary.description: The interface for objects which contain a set of items for which zero or more can be selected.

Interface Summary.name: KeyEventDispatcher
Interface Summary.description: A KeyEventDispatcher cooperates with the current KeyboardFocusManager in the targeting and dispatching of all KeyEvents.

Interface Summary.name: KeyEventPostProcessor
Interface Summary.description: A KeyEventPostProcessor cooperates with the current KeyboardFocusManager in the final resolution of all unconsumed KeyEvents.

Interface Summary.name: LayoutManager
Interface Summary.description: Defines the interface for classes that know how to lay out Containers.

Interface Summary.name: LayoutManager2
Interface Summary.description: Defines an interface for classes that know how to layout Containers based on a layout constraints object.

Interface Summary.name: MenuContainer
Interface Summary.description: The super class of all menu related containers.

Interface Summary.name: Paint
Interface Summary.description: This Paint interface defines how color patterns can be generated for Graphics2D operations.

Interface Summary.name: PaintContext
Interface Summary.description: The PaintContext interface defines the encapsulated and optimized environment to generate color patterns in device space for fill or stroke operations on a Graphics2D.

Interface Summary.name: PrintGraphics
Interface Summary.description: An abstract class which provides a print graphics context for a page.

Interface Summary.name: SecondaryLoop
Interface Summary.description: A helper interface to run the nested event loop.

Interface Summary.name: Shape
Interface Summary.description: The Shape interface provides definitions for objects that represent some form of geometric shape.

Interface Summary.name: Stroke
Interface Summary.description: The Stroke interface allows a Graphics2D object to obtain a Shape that is the decorated outline, or stylistic representation of the outline, of the specified Shape.

Interface Summary.name: Transparency
Interface Summary.description: The Transparency interface defines the common transparency modes for implementing classes.

Class Summary.name: AlphaComposite
Class Summary.description: The AlphaComposite class implements basic alpha compositing rules for combining source and destination colors to achieve blending and transparency effects with graphics and images.

Class Summary.name: AWTEvent
Class Summary.description: The root event class for all AWT events.

Class Summary.name: AWTEventMulticaster
Class Summary.description: AWTEventMulticaster implements efficient and thread-safe multi-cast event dispatching for the AWT events defined in the java.awt.event package.

Class Summary.name: AWTKeyStroke
Class Summary.description: An AWTKeyStroke represents a key action on the keyboard, or equivalent input device.

Class Summary.name: AWTPermission
Class Summary.description: This class is for AWT permissions.

Class Summary.name: BasicStroke
Class Summary.description: The BasicStroke class defines a basic set of rendering attributes for the outlines of graphics primitives, which are rendered with a Graphics2D object that has its Stroke attribute set to this BasicStroke.

Class Summary.name: BorderLayout
Class Summary.description: A border layout lays out a container, arranging and resizing its components to fit in five regions: north, south, east, west, and center.

Class Summary.name: BufferCapabilities
Class Summary.description: Capabilities and properties of buffers.

Class Summary.name: BufferCapabilities.FlipContents
Class Summary.description: A type-safe enumeration of the possible back buffer contents after page-flipping

Class Summary.name: Button
Class Summary.description: This class creates a labeled button.

Class Summary.name: Canvas
Class Summary.description: A Canvas component represents a blank rectangular area of the screen onto which the application can draw or from which the application can trap input events from the user.

Class Summary.name: CardLayout
Class Summary.description: A CardLayout object is a layout manager for a container.

Class Summary.name: Checkbox
Class Summary.description: A check box is a graphical component that can be in either an "on" (true) or "off" (false) state.

Class Summary.name: CheckboxGroup
Class Summary.description: The CheckboxGroup class is used to group together a set of Checkbox buttons.

Class Summary.name: CheckboxMenuItem
Class Summary.description: This class represents a check box that can be included in a menu.

Class Summary.name: Choice
Class Summary.description: The Choice class presents a pop-up menu of choices.

Class Summary.name: Color
Class Summary.description: The Color class is used to encapsulate colors in the default sRGB color space or colors in arbitrary color spaces identified by a ColorSpace.

Class Summary.name: Component
Class Summary.description: A component is an object having a graphical representation that can be displayed on the screen and that can interact with the user.

Class Summary.name: ComponentOrientation
Class Summary.description: The ComponentOrientation class encapsulates the language-sensitive orientation that is to be used to order the elements of a component or of text.

Class Summary.name: Container
Class Summary.description: A generic Abstract Window Toolkit(AWT) container object is a component that can contain other AWT components.

Class Summary.name: ContainerOrderFocusTraversalPolicy
Class Summary.description: A FocusTraversalPolicy that determines traversal order based on the order of child Components in a Container.

Class Summary.name: Cursor
Class Summary.description: A class to encapsulate the bitmap representation of the mouse cursor.

Class Summary.name: DefaultFocusTraversalPolicy
Class Summary.description: A FocusTraversalPolicy that determines traversal order based on the order of child Components in a Container.

Class Summary.name: DefaultKeyboardFocusManager
Class Summary.description: The default KeyboardFocusManager for AWT applications.

Class Summary.name: Desktop
Class Summary.description: The Desktop class allows a Java application to launch associated applications registered on the native desktop to handle a URI or a file.

Class Summary.name: Dialog
Class Summary.description: A Dialog is a top-level window with a title and a border that is typically used to take some form of input from the user.

Class Summary.name: Dimension
Class Summary.description: The Dimension class encapsulates the width and height of a component (in integer precision) in a single object.

Class Summary.name: DisplayMode
Class Summary.description: The DisplayMode class encapsulates the bit depth, height, width, and refresh rate of a GraphicsDevice.

Class Summary.name: Event
Class Summary.description: NOTE: The Event class is obsolete and is available only for backwards compatibility.

Class Summary.name: EventQueue
Class Summary.description: EventQueue is a platform-independent class that queues events, both from the underlying peer classes and from trusted application classes.

Class Summary.name: FileDialog
Class Summary.description: The FileDialog class displays a dialog window from which the user can select a file.

Class Summary.name: FlowLayout
Class Summary.description: A flow layout arranges components in a directional flow, much like lines of text in a paragraph.

Class Summary.name: FocusTraversalPolicy
Class Summary.description: A FocusTraversalPolicy defines the order in which Components with a particular focus cycle root are traversed.

Class Summary.name: Font
Class Summary.description: The Font class represents fonts, which are used to render text in a visible way.

Class Summary.name: FontMetrics
Class Summary.description: The FontMetrics class defines a font metrics object, which encapsulates information about the rendering of a particular font on a particular screen.

Class Summary.name: Frame
Class Summary.description: A Frame is a top-level window with a title and a border.

Class Summary.name: GradientPaint
Class Summary.description: The GradientPaint class provides a way to fill a Shape with a linear color gradient pattern.

Class Summary.name: Graphics
Class Summary.description: The Graphics class is the abstract base class for all graphics contexts that allow an application to draw onto components that are realized on various devices, as well as onto off-screen images.

Class Summary.name: Graphics2D
Class Summary.description: This Graphics2D class extends the Graphics class to provide more sophisticated control over geometry, coordinate transformations, color management, and text layout.

Class Summary.name: GraphicsConfigTemplate
Class Summary.description: The GraphicsConfigTemplate class is used to obtain a valid GraphicsConfiguration.

Class Summary.name: GraphicsConfiguration
Class Summary.description: The GraphicsConfiguration class describes the characteristics of a graphics destination such as a printer or monitor.

Class Summary.name: GraphicsDevice
Class Summary.description: The GraphicsDevice class describes the graphics devices that might be available in a particular graphics environment.

Class Summary.name: GraphicsEnvironment
Class Summary.description: The GraphicsEnvironment class describes the collection of GraphicsDevice objects and Font objects available to a Java(tm) application on a particular platform.

Class Summary.name: GridBagConstraints
Class Summary.description: The GridBagConstraints class specifies constraints for components that are laid out using the GridBagLayout class.

Class Summary.name: GridBagLayout
Class Summary.description: The GridBagLayout class is a flexible layout manager that aligns components vertically, horizontally or along their baseline without requiring that the components be of the same size.

Class Summary.name: GridBagLayoutInfo
Class Summary.description: The GridBagLayoutInfo is an utility class for GridBagLayout layout manager.

Class Summary.name: GridLayout
Class Summary.description: The GridLayout class is a layout manager that lays out a container's components in a rectangular grid.

Class Summary.name: Image
Class Summary.description: The abstract class Image is the superclass of all classes that represent graphical images.

Class Summary.name: ImageCapabilities
Class Summary.description: Capabilities and properties of images.

Class Summary.name: Insets
Class Summary.description: An Insets object is a representation of the borders of a container.

Class Summary.name: JobAttributes
Class Summary.description: A set of attributes which control a print job.

Class Summary.name: JobAttributes.DefaultSelectionType
Class Summary.description: A type-safe enumeration of possible default selection states.

Class Summary.name: JobAttributes.DestinationType
Class Summary.description: A type-safe enumeration of possible job destinations.

Class Summary.name: JobAttributes.DialogType
Class Summary.description: A type-safe enumeration of possible dialogs to display to the user.

Class Summary.name: JobAttributes.MultipleDocumentHandlingType
Class Summary.description: A type-safe enumeration of possible multiple copy handling states.

Class Summary.name: JobAttributes.SidesType
Class Summary.description: A type-safe enumeration of possible multi-page impositions.

Class Summary.name: KeyboardFocusManager
Class Summary.description: The KeyboardFocusManager is responsible for managing the active and focused Windows, and the current focus owner.

Class Summary.name: Label
Class Summary.description: A Label object is a component for placing text in a container.

Class Summary.name: LinearGradientPaint
Class Summary.description: The LinearGradientPaint class provides a way to fill a Shape with a linear color gradient pattern.

Class Summary.name: List
Class Summary.description: The List component presents the user with a scrolling list of text items.

Class Summary.name: MediaTracker
Class Summary.description: The MediaTracker class is a utility class to track the status of a number of media objects.

Class Summary.name: Menu
Class Summary.description: A Menu object is a pull-down menu component that is deployed from a menu bar.

Class Summary.name: MenuBar
Class Summary.description: The MenuBar class encapsulates the platform's concept of a menu bar bound to a frame.

Class Summary.name: MenuComponent
Class Summary.description: The abstract class MenuComponent is the superclass of all menu-related components.

Class Summary.name: MenuItem
Class Summary.description: All items in a menu must belong to the class MenuItem, or one of its subclasses.

Class Summary.name: MenuShortcut
Class Summary.description: The MenuShortcutclass represents a keyboard accelerator for a MenuItem.

Class Summary.name: MouseInfo
Class Summary.description: MouseInfo provides methods for getting information about the mouse, such as mouse pointer location and the number of mouse buttons.

Class Summary.name: MultipleGradientPaint
Class Summary.description: This is the superclass for Paints which use a multiple color gradient to fill in their raster.

Class Summary.name: PageAttributes
Class Summary.description: A set of attributes which control the output of a printed page.

Class Summary.name: PageAttributes.ColorType
Class Summary.description: A type-safe enumeration of possible color states.

Class Summary.name: PageAttributes.MediaType
Class Summary.description: A type-safe enumeration of possible paper sizes.

Class Summary.name: PageAttributes.OrientationRequestedType
Class Summary.description: A type-safe enumeration of possible orientations.

Class Summary.name: PageAttributes.OriginType
Class Summary.description: A type-safe enumeration of possible origins.

Class Summary.name: PageAttributes.PrintQualityType
Class Summary.description: A type-safe enumeration of possible print qualities.

Class Summary.name: Panel
Class Summary.description: Panel is the simplest container class.

Class Summary.name: Point
Class Summary.description: A point representing a location in (x,y) coordinate space, specified in integer precision.

Class Summary.name: PointerInfo
Class Summary.description: A class that describes the pointer position.

Class Summary.name: Polygon
Class Summary.description: The Polygon class encapsulates a description of a closed, two-dimensional region within a coordinate space.

Class Summary.name: PopupMenu
Class Summary.description: A class that implements a menu which can be dynamically popped up at a specified position within a component.

Class Summary.name: PrintJob
Class Summary.description: An abstract class which initiates and executes a print job.

Class Summary.name: RadialGradientPaint
Class Summary.description: The RadialGradientPaint class provides a way to fill a shape with a circular radial color gradient pattern.

Class Summary.name: Rectangle
Class Summary.description: A Rectangle specifies an area in a coordinate space that is enclosed by the Rectangle object's upper-left point (x,y) in the coordinate space, its width, and its height.

Class Summary.name: RenderingHints
Class Summary.description: The RenderingHints class defines and manages collections of keys and associated values which allow an application to provide input into the choice of algorithms used by other classes which perform rendering and image manipulation services.

Class Summary.name: RenderingHints.Key
Class Summary.description: Defines the base type of all keys used along with the RenderingHints class to control various algorithm choices in the rendering and imaging pipelines.

Class Summary.name: Robot
Class Summary.description: This class is used to generate native system input events for the purposes of test automation, self-running demos, and other applications where control of the mouse and keyboard is needed.

Class Summary.name: Scrollbar
Class Summary.description: The Scrollbar class embodies a scroll bar, a familiar user-interface object.

Class Summary.name: ScrollPane
Class Summary.description: A container class which implements automatic horizontal and/or vertical scrolling for a single child component.

Class Summary.name: ScrollPaneAdjustable
Class Summary.description: This class represents the state of a horizontal or vertical scrollbar of a ScrollPane.

Class Summary.name: SplashScreen
Class Summary.description: The splash screen can be displayed at application startup, before the Java Virtual Machine (JVM) starts.

Class Summary.name: SystemColor
Class Summary.description: A class to encapsulate symbolic colors representing the color of native GUI objects on a system.

Class Summary.name: SystemTray
Class Summary.description: The SystemTray class represents the system tray for a desktop.

Class Summary.name: TextArea
Class Summary.description: A TextArea object is a multi-line region that displays text.

Class Summary.name: TextComponent
Class Summary.description: The TextComponent class is the superclass of any component that allows the editing of some text.

Class Summary.name: TextField
Class Summary.description: A TextField object is a text component that allows for the editing of a single line of text.

Class Summary.name: TexturePaint
Class Summary.description: The TexturePaint class provides a way to fill a Shape with a texture that is specified as a BufferedImage.

Class Summary.name: Toolkit
Class Summary.description: This class is the abstract superclass of all actual implementations of the Abstract Window Toolkit.

Class Summary.name: TrayIcon
Class Summary.description: A TrayIcon object represents a tray icon that can be added to the system tray.

Class Summary.name: Window
Class Summary.description: A Window object is a top-level window with no borders and no menubar.

Enum Summary.name: Component.BaselineResizeBehavior
Enum Summary.description: Enumeration of the common ways the baseline of a component can change as the size changes.

Enum Summary.name: Desktop.Action
Enum Summary.description: Represents an action type.

Enum Summary.name: Dialog.ModalExclusionType
Enum Summary.description: Any top-level window can be marked not to be blocked by modal dialogs.

Enum Summary.name: Dialog.ModalityType
Enum Summary.description: Modal dialogs block all input to some top-level windows.

Enum Summary.name: GraphicsDevice.WindowTranslucency
Enum Summary.description: Kinds of translucency supported by the underlying system.

Enum Summary.name: MultipleGradientPaint.ColorSpaceType
Enum Summary.description: The color space in which to perform the gradient interpolation.

Enum Summary.name: MultipleGradientPaint.CycleMethod
Enum Summary.description: The method to use when painting outside the gradient bounds.

Enum Summary.name: TrayIcon.MessageType
Enum Summary.description: The message type determines which icon will be displayed in the caption of the message, and a possible system sound a message may generate upon showing.

Enum Summary.name: Window.Type
Enum Summary.description: Enumeration of available window types.

Exception Summary.name: AWTException
Exception Summary.description: Signals that an Abstract Window Toolkit exception has occurred.

Exception Summary.name: FontFormatException
Exception Summary.description: Thrown by method createFont in the Font class to indicate that the specified font is bad.

Exception Summary.name: HeadlessException
Exception Summary.description: Thrown when code that is dependent on a keyboard, display, or mouse is called in an environment that does not support a keyboard, display, or mouse.

Exception Summary.name: IllegalComponentStateException
Exception Summary.description: Signals that an AWT component is not in an appropriate state for the requested operation.

Error Summary.name: AWTError
Error Summary.description: Thrown when a serious Abstract Window Toolkit error has occurred.

name: java.awt.color
description: Provides classes for color spaces.

Class Summary.name: ColorSpace
Class Summary.description: This abstract class is used to serve as a color space tag to identify the specific color space of a Color object or, via a ColorModel object, of an Image, a BufferedImage, or a GraphicsDevice.

Class Summary.name: ICC_ColorSpace
Class Summary.description: The ICC_ColorSpace class is an implementation of the abstract ColorSpace class.

Class Summary.name: ICC_Profile
Class Summary.description: A representation of color profile data for device independent and device dependent color spaces based on the International Color Consortium Specification ICC.1:2001-12, File Format for Color Profiles, (see http://www.color.org).

Class Summary.name: ICC_ProfileGray
Class Summary.description: A subclass of the ICC_Profile class which represents profiles which meet the following criteria: the color space type of the profile is TYPE_GRAY and the profile includes the grayTRCTag and mediaWhitePointTag tags.

Class Summary.name: ICC_ProfileRGB
Class Summary.description: The ICC_ProfileRGB class is a subclass of the ICC_Profile class that represents profiles which meet the following criteria: The profile's color space type is RGB. The profile includes the redColorantTag, greenColorantTag, blueColorantTag, redTRCTag, greenTRCTag, blueTRCTag, and mediaWhitePointTag tags. The ICC_Profile getInstance method will return an ICC_ProfileRGB object when these conditions are met.

Exception Summary.name: CMMException
Exception Summary.description: This exception is thrown if the native CMM returns an error.

Exception Summary.name: ProfileDataException
Exception Summary.description: This exception is thrown when an error occurs in accessing or processing an ICC_Profile object.

name: java.awt.datatransfer
description: Provides interfaces and classes for transferring data between and within applications.

Interface Summary.name: ClipboardOwner
Interface Summary.description: Defines the interface for classes that will provide data to a clipboard.

Interface Summary.name: FlavorListener
Interface Summary.description: Defines an object which listens for FlavorEvents.

Interface Summary.name: FlavorMap
Interface Summary.description: A two-way Map between "natives" (Strings), which correspond to platform- specific data formats, and "flavors" (DataFlavors), which correspond to platform-independent MIME types.

Interface Summary.name: FlavorTable
Interface Summary.description: A FlavorMap which relaxes the traditional 1-to-1 restriction of a Map.

Interface Summary.name: Transferable
Interface Summary.description: Defines the interface for classes that can be used to provide data for a transfer operation.

Class Summary.name: Clipboard
Class Summary.description: A class that implements a mechanism to transfer data using cut/copy/paste operations.

Class Summary.name: DataFlavor
Class Summary.description: A DataFlavor provides meta information about data.

Class Summary.name: FlavorEvent
Class Summary.description: FlavorEvent is used to notify interested parties that available DataFlavors have changed in the Clipboard (the event source).

Class Summary.name: StringSelection
Class Summary.description: A Transferable which implements the capability required to transfer a String.

Class Summary.name: SystemFlavorMap
Class Summary.description: The SystemFlavorMap is a configurable map between "natives" (Strings), which correspond to platform-specific data formats, and "flavors" (DataFlavors), which correspond to platform-independent MIME types.

Exception Summary.name: MimeTypeParseException
Exception Summary.description: A class to encapsulate MimeType parsing related exceptions

Exception Summary.name: UnsupportedFlavorException
Exception Summary.description: Signals that the requested data is not supported in this flavor.

name: java.awt.dnd
description: Drag and Drop is a direct manipulation gesture found in many Graphical User Interface systems that provides a mechanism to transfer information between two entities logically associated with presentation elements in the GUI.

Interface Summary.name: Autoscroll
Interface Summary.description: During DnD operations it is possible that a user may wish to drop the subject of the operation on a region of a scrollable GUI control that is not currently visible to the user.

Interface Summary.name: DragGestureListener
Interface Summary.description: The listener interface for receiving drag gesture events.

Interface Summary.name: DragSourceListener
Interface Summary.description: The DragSourceListener defines the event interface for originators of Drag and Drop operations to track the state of the user's gesture, and to provide appropriate "drag over" feedback to the user throughout the Drag and Drop operation.

Interface Summary.name: DragSourceMotionListener
Interface Summary.description: A listener interface for receiving mouse motion events during a drag operation.

Interface Summary.name: DropTargetListener
Interface Summary.description: The DropTargetListener interface is the callback interface used by the DropTarget class to provide notification of DnD operations that involve the subject DropTarget.

Class Summary.name: DnDConstants
Class Summary.description: This class contains constant values representing the type of action(s) to be performed by a Drag and Drop operation.

Class Summary.name: DragGestureEvent
Class Summary.description: A DragGestureEvent is passed to DragGestureListener's dragGestureRecognized() method when a particular DragGestureRecognizer detects that a platform dependent drag initiating gesture has occurred on the Component that it is tracking.

Class Summary.name: DragGestureRecognizer
Class Summary.description: The DragGestureRecognizer is an abstract base class for the specification of a platform-dependent listener that can be associated with a particular Component in order to identify platform-dependent drag initiating gestures.

Class Summary.name: DragSource
Class Summary.description: The DragSource is the entity responsible for the initiation of the Drag and Drop operation, and may be used in a number of scenarios: 1 default instance per JVM for the lifetime of that JVM.

Class Summary.name: DragSourceAdapter
Class Summary.description: An abstract adapter class for receiving drag source events.

Class Summary.name: DragSourceContext
Class Summary.description: The DragSourceContext class is responsible for managing the initiator side of the Drag and Drop protocol.

Class Summary.name: DragSourceDragEvent
Class Summary.description: The DragSourceDragEvent is delivered from the DragSourceContextPeer, via the DragSourceContext, to the DragSourceListener registered with that DragSourceContext and with its associated DragSource.

Class Summary.name: DragSourceDropEvent
Class Summary.description: The DragSourceDropEvent is delivered from the DragSourceContextPeer, via the DragSourceContext, to the dragDropEnd method of DragSourceListeners registered with that DragSourceContext and with its associated DragSource.

Class Summary.name: DragSourceEvent
Class Summary.description: This class is the base class for DragSourceDragEvent and DragSourceDropEvent.

Class Summary.name: DropTarget
Class Summary.description: The DropTarget is associated with a Component when that Component wishes to accept drops during Drag and Drop operations.

Class Summary.name: DropTarget.DropTargetAutoScroller
Class Summary.description: this protected nested class implements autoscrolling

Class Summary.name: DropTargetAdapter
Class Summary.description: An abstract adapter class for receiving drop target events.

Class Summary.name: DropTargetContext
Class Summary.description: A DropTargetContext is created whenever the logical cursor associated with a Drag and Drop operation coincides with the visible geometry of a Component associated with a DropTarget.

Class Summary.name: DropTargetDragEvent
Class Summary.description: The DropTargetDragEvent is delivered to a DropTargetListener via its dragEnter() and dragOver() methods.

Class Summary.name: DropTargetDropEvent
Class Summary.description: The DropTargetDropEvent is delivered via the DropTargetListener drop() method.

Class Summary.name: DropTargetEvent
Class Summary.description: The DropTargetEvent is the base class for both the DropTargetDragEvent and the DropTargetDropEvent.

Class Summary.name: MouseDragGestureRecognizer
Class Summary.description: This abstract subclass of DragGestureRecognizer defines a DragGestureRecognizer for mouse-based gestures.

Exception Summary.name: InvalidDnDOperationException
Exception Summary.description: This exception is thrown by various methods in the java.awt.dnd package.

name: java.awt.event
description: Provides interfaces and classes for dealing with different types of events fired by AWT components.

Interface Summary.name: ActionListener
Interface Summary.description: The listener interface for receiving action events.

Interface Summary.name: AdjustmentListener
Interface Summary.description: The listener interface for receiving adjustment events.

Interface Summary.name: AWTEventListener
Interface Summary.description: The listener interface for receiving notification of events dispatched to objects that are instances of Component or MenuComponent or their subclasses.

Interface Summary.name: ComponentListener
Interface Summary.description: The listener interface for receiving component events.

Interface Summary.name: ContainerListener
Interface Summary.description: The listener interface for receiving container events.

Interface Summary.name: FocusListener
Interface Summary.description: The listener interface for receiving keyboard focus events on a component.

Interface Summary.name: HierarchyBoundsListener
Interface Summary.description: The listener interface for receiving ancestor moved and resized events.

Interface Summary.name: HierarchyListener
Interface Summary.description: The listener interface for receiving hierarchy changed events.

Interface Summary.name: InputMethodListener
Interface Summary.description: The listener interface for receiving input method events.

Interface Summary.name: ItemListener
Interface Summary.description: The listener interface for receiving item events.

Interface Summary.name: KeyListener
Interface Summary.description: The listener interface for receiving keyboard events (keystrokes).

Interface Summary.name: MouseListener
Interface Summary.description: The listener interface for receiving "interesting" mouse events (press, release, click, enter, and exit) on a component.

Interface Summary.name: MouseMotionListener
Interface Summary.description: The listener interface for receiving mouse motion events on a component.

Interface Summary.name: MouseWheelListener
Interface Summary.description: The listener interface for receiving mouse wheel events on a component.

Interface Summary.name: TextListener
Interface Summary.description: The listener interface for receiving text events.

Interface Summary.name: WindowFocusListener
Interface Summary.description: The listener interface for receiving WindowEvents, including WINDOW_GAINED_FOCUS and WINDOW_LOST_FOCUS events.

Interface Summary.name: WindowListener
Interface Summary.description: The listener interface for receiving window events.

Interface Summary.name: WindowStateListener
Interface Summary.description: The listener interface for receiving window state events.

Class Summary.name: ActionEvent
Class Summary.description: A semantic event which indicates that a component-defined action occurred.

Class Summary.name: AdjustmentEvent
Class Summary.description: The adjustment event emitted by Adjustable objects like Scrollbar and ScrollPane.

Class Summary.name: AWTEventListenerProxy
Class Summary.description: A class which extends the EventListenerProxy specifically for adding an AWTEventListener for a specific event mask.

Class Summary.name: ComponentAdapter
Class Summary.description: An abstract adapter class for receiving component events.

Class Summary.name: ComponentEvent
Class Summary.description: A low-level event which indicates that a component moved, changed size, or changed visibility (also, the root class for the other component-level events).

Class Summary.name: ContainerAdapter
Class Summary.description: An abstract adapter class for receiving container events.

Class Summary.name: ContainerEvent
Class Summary.description: A low-level event which indicates that a container's contents changed because a component was added or removed.

Class Summary.name: FocusAdapter
Class Summary.description: An abstract adapter class for receiving keyboard focus events.

Class Summary.name: FocusEvent
Class Summary.description: A low-level event which indicates that a Component has gained or lost the input focus.

Class Summary.name: HierarchyBoundsAdapter
Class Summary.description: An abstract adapter class for receiving ancestor moved and resized events.

Class Summary.name: HierarchyEvent
Class Summary.description: An event which indicates a change to the Component hierarchy to which Component belongs.

Class Summary.name: InputEvent
Class Summary.description: The root event class for all component-level input events.

Class Summary.name: InputMethodEvent
Class Summary.description: Input method events contain information about text that is being composed using an input method.

Class Summary.name: InvocationEvent
Class Summary.description: An event which executes the run() method on a Runnable when dispatched by the AWT event dispatcher thread.

Class Summary.name: ItemEvent
Class Summary.description: A semantic event which indicates that an item was selected or deselected.

Class Summary.name: KeyAdapter
Class Summary.description: An abstract adapter class for receiving keyboard events.

Class Summary.name: KeyEvent
Class Summary.description: An event which indicates that a keystroke occurred in a component.

Class Summary.name: MouseAdapter
Class Summary.description: An abstract adapter class for receiving mouse events.

Class Summary.name: MouseEvent
Class Summary.description: An event which indicates that a mouse action occurred in a component.

Class Summary.name: MouseMotionAdapter
Class Summary.description: An abstract adapter class for receiving mouse motion events.

Class Summary.name: MouseWheelEvent
Class Summary.description: An event which indicates that the mouse wheel was rotated in a component.

Class Summary.name: PaintEvent
Class Summary.description: The component-level paint event.

Class Summary.name: TextEvent
Class Summary.description: A semantic event which indicates that an object's text changed.

Class Summary.name: WindowAdapter
Class Summary.description: An abstract adapter class for receiving window events.

Class Summary.name: WindowEvent
Class Summary.description: A low-level event that indicates that a window has changed its status.

name: java.awt.font
description: Provides classes and interface relating to fonts.

Interface Summary.name: MultipleMaster
Interface Summary.description: The MultipleMaster interface represents Type 1 Multiple Master fonts.

Interface Summary.name: OpenType
Interface Summary.description: The OpenType interface represents OpenType and TrueType fonts.

Class Summary.name: FontRenderContext
Class Summary.description: The FontRenderContext class is a container for the information needed to correctly measure text.

Class Summary.name: GlyphJustificationInfo
Class Summary.description: The GlyphJustificationInfo class represents information about the justification properties of a glyph.

Class Summary.name: GlyphMetrics
Class Summary.description: The GlyphMetrics class represents information for a single glyph.

Class Summary.name: GlyphVector
Class Summary.description: A GlyphVector object is a collection of glyphs containing geometric information for the placement of each glyph in a transformed coordinate space which corresponds to the device on which the GlyphVector is ultimately displayed.

Class Summary.name: GraphicAttribute
Class Summary.description: This class is used with the CHAR_REPLACEMENT attribute.

Class Summary.name: ImageGraphicAttribute
Class Summary.description: The ImageGraphicAttribute class is an implementation of GraphicAttribute which draws images in a TextLayout.

Class Summary.name: LayoutPath
Class Summary.description: LayoutPath provides a mapping between locations relative to the baseline and points in user space.

Class Summary.name: LineBreakMeasurer
Class Summary.description: The LineBreakMeasurer class allows styled text to be broken into lines (or segments) that fit within a particular visual advance.

Class Summary.name: LineMetrics
Class Summary.description: The LineMetrics class allows access to the metrics needed to layout characters along a line and to layout of a set of lines.

Class Summary.name: NumericShaper
Class Summary.description: The NumericShaper class is used to convert Latin-1 (European) digits to other Unicode decimal digits.

Class Summary.name: ShapeGraphicAttribute
Class Summary.description: The ShapeGraphicAttribute class is an implementation of GraphicAttribute that draws shapes in a TextLayout.

Class Summary.name: TextAttribute
Class Summary.description: The TextAttribute class defines attribute keys and attribute values used for text rendering.

Class Summary.name: TextHitInfo
Class Summary.description: The TextHitInfo class represents a character position in a text model, and a bias, or "side," of the character.

Class Summary.name: TextLayout
Class Summary.description: TextLayout is an immutable graphical representation of styled character data.

Class Summary.name: TextLayout.CaretPolicy
Class Summary.description: Defines a policy for determining the strong caret location.

Class Summary.name: TextMeasurer
Class Summary.description: The TextMeasurer class provides the primitive operations needed for line break: measuring up to a given advance, determining the advance of a range of characters, and generating a TextLayout for a range of characters.

Class Summary.name: TransformAttribute
Class Summary.description: The TransformAttribute class provides an immutable wrapper for a transform so that it is safe to use as an attribute.

Enum Summary.name: NumericShaper.Range
Enum Summary.description: A NumericShaper.Range represents a Unicode range of a script having its own decimal digits.

name: java.awt.geom
description: Provides the Java 2D classes for defining and performing operations on objects related to two-dimensional geometry.

Interface Summary.name: PathIterator
Interface Summary.description: The PathIterator interface provides the mechanism for objects that implement the Shape interface to return the geometry of their boundary by allowing a caller to retrieve the path of that boundary a segment at a time.

Class Summary.name: AffineTransform
Class Summary.description: The AffineTransform class represents a 2D affine transform that performs a linear mapping from 2D coordinates to other 2D coordinates that preserves the "straightness" and "parallelness" of lines.

Class Summary.name: Arc2D
Class Summary.description: Arc2D is the abstract superclass for all objects that store a 2D arc defined by a framing rectangle, start angle, angular extent (length of the arc), and a closure type (OPEN, CHORD, or PIE).

Class Summary.name: Arc2D.Double
Class Summary.description: This class defines an arc specified in double precision.

Class Summary.name: Arc2D.Float
Class Summary.description: This class defines an arc specified in float precision.

Class Summary.name: Area
Class Summary.description: An Area object stores and manipulates a resolution-independent description of an enclosed area of 2-dimensional space.

Class Summary.name: CubicCurve2D
Class Summary.description: The CubicCurve2D class defines a cubic parametric curve segment in (x,y) coordinate space.

Class Summary.name: CubicCurve2D.Double
Class Summary.description: A cubic parametric curve segment specified with double coordinates.

Class Summary.name: CubicCurve2D.Float
Class Summary.description: A cubic parametric curve segment specified with float coordinates.

Class Summary.name: Dimension2D
Class Summary.description: The Dimension2D class is to encapsulate a width and a height dimension.

Class Summary.name: Ellipse2D
Class Summary.description: The Ellipse2D class describes an ellipse that is defined by a framing rectangle.

Class Summary.name: Ellipse2D.Double
Class Summary.description: The Double class defines an ellipse specified in double precision.

Class Summary.name: Ellipse2D.Float
Class Summary.description: The Float class defines an ellipse specified in float precision.

Class Summary.name: FlatteningPathIterator
Class Summary.description: The FlatteningPathIterator class returns a flattened view of another PathIterator object.

Class Summary.name: GeneralPath
Class Summary.description: The GeneralPath class represents a geometric path constructed from straight lines, and quadratic and cubic (Bzier) curves.

Class Summary.name: Line2D
Class Summary.description: This Line2D represents a line segment in (x,y) coordinate space.

Class Summary.name: Line2D.Double
Class Summary.description: A line segment specified with double coordinates.

Class Summary.name: Line2D.Float
Class Summary.description: A line segment specified with float coordinates.

Class Summary.name: Path2D
Class Summary.description: The Path2D class provides a simple, yet flexible shape which represents an arbitrary geometric path.

Class Summary.name: Path2D.Double
Class Summary.description: The Double class defines a geometric path with coordinates stored in double precision floating point.

Class Summary.name: Path2D.Float
Class Summary.description: The Float class defines a geometric path with coordinates stored in single precision floating point.

Class Summary.name: Point2D
Class Summary.description: The Point2D class defines a point representing a location in (x,y) coordinate space.

Class Summary.name: Point2D.Double
Class Summary.description: The Double class defines a point specified in double precision.

Class Summary.name: Point2D.Float
Class Summary.description: The Float class defines a point specified in float precision.

Class Summary.name: QuadCurve2D
Class Summary.description: The QuadCurve2D class defines a quadratic parametric curve segment in (x,y) coordinate space.

Class Summary.name: QuadCurve2D.Double
Class Summary.description: A quadratic parametric curve segment specified with double coordinates.

Class Summary.name: QuadCurve2D.Float
Class Summary.description: A quadratic parametric curve segment specified with float coordinates.

Class Summary.name: Rectangle2D
Class Summary.description: The Rectangle2D class describes a rectangle defined by a location (x,y) and dimension (w x h).

Class Summary.name: Rectangle2D.Double
Class Summary.description: The Double class defines a rectangle specified in double coordinates.

Class Summary.name: Rectangle2D.Float
Class Summary.description: The Float class defines a rectangle specified in float coordinates.

Class Summary.name: RectangularShape
Class Summary.description: RectangularShape is the base class for a number of Shape objects whose geometry is defined by a rectangular frame.

Class Summary.name: RoundRectangle2D
Class Summary.description: The RoundRectangle2D class defines a rectangle with rounded corners defined by a location (x,y), a dimension (w x h), and the width and height of an arc with which to round the corners.

Class Summary.name: RoundRectangle2D.Double
Class Summary.description: The Double class defines a rectangle with rounded corners all specified in double coordinates.

Class Summary.name: RoundRectangle2D.Float
Class Summary.description: The Float class defines a rectangle with rounded corners all specified in float coordinates.

Exception Summary.name: IllegalPathStateException
Exception Summary.description: The IllegalPathStateException represents an exception that is thrown if an operation is performed on a path that is in an illegal state with respect to the particular operation being performed, such as appending a path segment to a GeneralPath without an initial moveto.

Exception Summary.name: NoninvertibleTransformException
Exception Summary.description: The NoninvertibleTransformException class represents an exception that is thrown if an operation is performed requiring the inverse of an AffineTransform object but the AffineTransform is in a non-invertible state.

name: java.awt.im
description: Provides classes and interfaces for the input method framework.

Interface Summary.name: InputMethodRequests
Interface Summary.description: InputMethodRequests defines the requests that a text editing component has to handle in order to work with input methods.

Class Summary.name: InputContext
Class Summary.description: Provides methods to control text input facilities such as input methods and keyboard layouts.

Class Summary.name: InputMethodHighlight
Class Summary.description: An InputMethodHighlight is used to describe the highlight attributes of text being composed.

Class Summary.name: InputSubset
Class Summary.description: Defines additional Unicode subsets for use by input methods.

name: java.awt.im.spi
description: Provides interfaces that enable the development of input methods that can be used with any Java runtime environment.

Interface Summary.name: InputMethod
Interface Summary.description: Defines the interface for an input method that supports complex text input.

Interface Summary.name: InputMethodContext
Interface Summary.description: Provides methods that input methods can use to communicate with their client components or to request other services.

Interface Summary.name: InputMethodDescriptor
Interface Summary.description: Defines methods that provide sufficient information about an input method to enable selection and loading of that input method.

name: java.awt.image
description: Provides classes for creating and modifying images.

Interface Summary.name: BufferedImageOp
Interface Summary.description: This interface describes single-input/single-output operations performed on BufferedImage objects.

Interface Summary.name: ImageConsumer
Interface Summary.description: The interface for objects expressing interest in image data through the ImageProducer interfaces.

Interface Summary.name: ImageObserver
Interface Summary.description: An asynchronous update interface for receiving notifications about Image information as the Image is constructed.

Interface Summary.name: ImageProducer
Interface Summary.description: The interface for objects which can produce the image data for Images.

Interface Summary.name: RasterOp
Interface Summary.description: This interface describes single-input/single-output operations performed on Raster objects.

Interface Summary.name: RenderedImage
Interface Summary.description: RenderedImage is a common interface for objects which contain or can produce image data in the form of Rasters.

Interface Summary.name: TileObserver
Interface Summary.description: An interface for objects that wish to be informed when tiles of a WritableRenderedImage become modifiable by some writer via a call to getWritableTile, and when they become unmodifiable via the last call to releaseWritableTile.

Interface Summary.name: WritableRenderedImage
Interface Summary.description: WriteableRenderedImage is a common interface for objects which contain or can produce image data in the form of Rasters and which can be modified and/or written over.

Class Summary.name: AffineTransformOp
Class Summary.description: This class uses an affine transform to perform a linear mapping from 2D coordinates in the source image or Raster to 2D coordinates in the destination image or Raster.

Class Summary.name: AreaAveragingScaleFilter
Class Summary.description: An ImageFilter class for scaling images using a simple area averaging algorithm that produces smoother results than the nearest neighbor algorithm.

Class Summary.name: BandCombineOp
Class Summary.description: This class performs an arbitrary linear combination of the bands in a Raster, using a specified matrix.

Class Summary.name: BandedSampleModel
Class Summary.description: This class represents image data which is stored in a band interleaved fashion and for which each sample of a pixel occupies one data element of the DataBuffer.

Class Summary.name: BufferedImage
Class Summary.description: The BufferedImage subclass describes an Image with an accessible buffer of image data.

Class Summary.name: BufferedImageFilter
Class Summary.description: The BufferedImageFilter class subclasses an ImageFilter to provide a simple means of using a single-source/single-destination image operator (BufferedImageOp) to filter a BufferedImage in the Image Producer/Consumer/Observer paradigm.

Class Summary.name: BufferStrategy
Class Summary.description: The BufferStrategy class represents the mechanism with which to organize complex memory on a particular Canvas or Window.

Class Summary.name: ByteLookupTable
Class Summary.description: This class defines a lookup table object.

Class Summary.name: ColorConvertOp
Class Summary.description: This class performs a pixel-by-pixel color conversion of the data in the source image.

Class Summary.name: ColorModel
Class Summary.description: The ColorModel abstract class encapsulates the methods for translating a pixel value to color components (for example, red, green, and blue) and an alpha component.

Class Summary.name: ComponentColorModel
Class Summary.description: A ColorModel class that works with pixel values that represent color and alpha information as separate samples and that store each sample in a separate data element.

Class Summary.name: ComponentSampleModel
Class Summary.description: This class represents image data which is stored such that each sample of a pixel occupies one data element of the DataBuffer.

Class Summary.name: ConvolveOp
Class Summary.description: This class implements a convolution from the source to the destination.

Class Summary.name: CropImageFilter
Class Summary.description: An ImageFilter class for cropping images.

Class Summary.name: DataBuffer
Class Summary.description: This class exists to wrap one or more data arrays.

Class Summary.name: DataBufferByte
Class Summary.description: This class extends DataBuffer and stores data internally as bytes.

Class Summary.name: DataBufferDouble
Class Summary.description: This class extends DataBuffer and stores data internally in double form.

Class Summary.name: DataBufferFloat
Class Summary.description: This class extends DataBuffer and stores data internally in float form.

Class Summary.name: DataBufferInt
Class Summary.description: This class extends DataBuffer and stores data internally as integers.

Class Summary.name: DataBufferShort
Class Summary.description: This class extends DataBuffer and stores data internally as shorts.

Class Summary.name: DataBufferUShort
Class Summary.description: This class extends DataBuffer and stores data internally as shorts.

Class Summary.name: DirectColorModel
Class Summary.description: The DirectColorModel class is a ColorModel class that works with pixel values that represent RGB color and alpha information as separate samples and that pack all samples for a single pixel into a single int, short, or byte quantity.

Class Summary.name: FilteredImageSource
Class Summary.description: This class is an implementation of the ImageProducer interface which takes an existing image and a filter object and uses them to produce image data for a new filtered version of the original image.

Class Summary.name: ImageFilter
Class Summary.description: This class implements a filter for the set of interface methods that are used to deliver data from an ImageProducer to an ImageConsumer.

Class Summary.name: IndexColorModel
Class Summary.description: The IndexColorModel class is a ColorModel class that works with pixel values consisting of a single sample that is an index into a fixed colormap in the default sRGB color space.

Class Summary.name: Kernel
Class Summary.description: The Kernel class defines a matrix that describes how a specified pixel and its surrounding pixels affect the value computed for the pixel's position in the output image of a filtering operation.

Class Summary.name: LookupOp
Class Summary.description: This class implements a lookup operation from the source to the destination.

Class Summary.name: LookupTable
Class Summary.description: This abstract class defines a lookup table object.

Class Summary.name: MemoryImageSource
Class Summary.description: This class is an implementation of the ImageProducer interface which uses an array to produce pixel values for an Image.

Class Summary.name: MultiPixelPackedSampleModel
Class Summary.description: The MultiPixelPackedSampleModel class represents one-banded images and can pack multiple one-sample pixels into one data element.

Class Summary.name: PackedColorModel
Class Summary.description: The PackedColorModel class is an abstract ColorModel class that works with pixel values which represent color and alpha information as separate samples and which pack all samples for a single pixel into a single int, short, or byte quantity.

Class Summary.name: PixelGrabber
Class Summary.description: The PixelGrabber class implements an ImageConsumer which can be attached to an Image or ImageProducer object to retrieve a subset of the pixels in that image.

Class Summary.name: PixelInterleavedSampleModel
Class Summary.description: This class represents image data which is stored in a pixel interleaved fashion and for which each sample of a pixel occupies one data element of the DataBuffer.

Class Summary.name: Raster
Class Summary.description: A class representing a rectangular array of pixels.

Class Summary.name: ReplicateScaleFilter
Class Summary.description: An ImageFilter class for scaling images using the simplest algorithm.

Class Summary.name: RescaleOp
Class Summary.description: This class performs a pixel-by-pixel rescaling of the data in the source image by multiplying the sample values for each pixel by a scale factor and then adding an offset.

Class Summary.name: RGBImageFilter
Class Summary.description: This class provides an easy way to create an ImageFilter which modifies the pixels of an image in the default RGB ColorModel.

Class Summary.name: SampleModel
Class Summary.description: This abstract class defines an interface for extracting samples of pixels in an image.

Class Summary.name: ShortLookupTable
Class Summary.description: This class defines a lookup table object.

Class Summary.name: SinglePixelPackedSampleModel
Class Summary.description: This class represents pixel data packed such that the N samples which make up a single pixel are stored in a single data array element, and each data data array element holds samples for only one pixel.

Class Summary.name: VolatileImage
Class Summary.description: VolatileImage is an image which can lose its contents at any time due to circumstances beyond the control of the application (e.g., situations caused by the operating system or by other applications).

Class Summary.name: WritableRaster
Class Summary.description: This class extends Raster to provide pixel writing capabilities.

Exception Summary.name: ImagingOpException
Exception Summary.description: The ImagingOpException is thrown if one of the BufferedImageOp or RasterOp filter methods cannot process the image.

Exception Summary.name: RasterFormatException
Exception Summary.description: The RasterFormatException is thrown if there is invalid layout information in the Raster.

name: java.awt.image.renderable
description: Provides classes and interfaces for producing rendering-independent images.

Interface Summary.name: ContextualRenderedImageFactory
Interface Summary.description: ContextualRenderedImageFactory provides an interface for the functionality that may differ between instances of RenderableImageOp.

Interface Summary.name: RenderableImage
Interface Summary.description: A RenderableImage is a common interface for rendering-independent images (a notion which subsumes resolution independence).

Interface Summary.name: RenderedImageFactory
Interface Summary.description: The RenderedImageFactory interface (often abbreviated RIF) is intended to be implemented by classes that wish to act as factories to produce different renderings, for example by executing a series of BufferedImageOps on a set of sources, depending on a specific set of parameters, properties, and rendering hints.

Class Summary.name: ParameterBlock
Class Summary.description: A ParameterBlock encapsulates all the information about sources and parameters (Objects) required by a RenderableImageOp, or other classes that process images.

Class Summary.name: RenderableImageOp
Class Summary.description: This class handles the renderable aspects of an operation with help from its associated instance of a ContextualRenderedImageFactory.

Class Summary.name: RenderableImageProducer
Class Summary.description: An adapter class that implements ImageProducer to allow the asynchronous production of a RenderableImage.

Class Summary.name: RenderContext
Class Summary.description: A RenderContext encapsulates the information needed to produce a specific rendering from a RenderableImage.

name: java.awt.print
description: Provides classes and interfaces for a general printing API.

Interface Summary.name: Pageable
Interface Summary.description: The Pageable implementation represents a set of pages to be printed.

Interface Summary.name: Printable
Interface Summary.description: The Printable interface is implemented by the print methods of the current page painter, which is called by the printing system to render a page.

Interface Summary.name: PrinterGraphics
Interface Summary.description: The PrinterGraphics interface is implemented by Graphics objects that are passed to Printable objects to render a page.

Class Summary.name: Book
Class Summary.description: The Book class provides a representation of a document in which pages may have different page formats and page painters.

Class Summary.name: PageFormat
Class Summary.description: The PageFormat class describes the size and orientation of a page to be printed.

Class Summary.name: Paper
Class Summary.description: The Paper class describes the physical characteristics of a piece of paper.

Class Summary.name: PrinterJob
Class Summary.description: The PrinterJob class is the principal class that controls printing.

Exception Summary.name: PrinterAbortException
Exception Summary.description: The PrinterAbortException class is a subclass of PrinterException and is used to indicate that a user or application has terminated the print job while it was in the process of printing.

Exception Summary.name: PrinterException
Exception Summary.description: The PrinterException class and its subclasses are used to indicate that an exceptional condition has occurred in the print system.

Exception Summary.name: PrinterIOException
Exception Summary.description: The PrinterIOException class is a subclass of PrinterException and is used to indicate that an IO error of some sort has occurred while printing.

name: java.beans
description: Contains classes related to developing beans -- components based on the JavaBeans architecture.

Interface Summary.name: AppletInitializer
Interface Summary.description: This interface is designed to work in collusion with java.beans.Beans.instantiate.

Interface Summary.name: BeanInfo
Interface Summary.description: Use the BeanInfo interface to create a BeanInfo class and provide explicit information about the methods, properties, events, and other features of your beans.

Interface Summary.name: Customizer
Interface Summary.description: A customizer class provides a complete custom GUI for customizing a target Java Bean.

Interface Summary.name: DesignMode
Interface Summary.description: This interface is intended to be implemented by, or delegated from, instances of java.beans.beancontext.BeanContext, in order to propagate to its nested hierarchy of java.beans.beancontext.BeanContextChild instances, the current "designTime" property.

Interface Summary.name: ExceptionListener
Interface Summary.description: An ExceptionListener is notified of internal exceptions.

Interface Summary.name: PropertyChangeListener
Interface Summary.description: A "PropertyChange" event gets fired whenever a bean changes a "bound" property.

Interface Summary.name: PropertyEditor
Interface Summary.description: A PropertyEditor class provides support for GUIs that want to allow users to edit a property value of a given type.

Interface Summary.name: VetoableChangeListener
Interface Summary.description: A VetoableChange event gets fired whenever a bean changes a "constrained" property.

Interface Summary.name: Visibility
Interface Summary.description: Under some circumstances a bean may be run on servers where a GUI is not available.

Class Summary.name: BeanDescriptor
Class Summary.description: A BeanDescriptor provides global information about a "bean", including its Java class, its displayName, etc.

Class Summary.name: Beans
Class Summary.description: This class provides some general purpose beans control methods.

Class Summary.name: DefaultPersistenceDelegate
Class Summary.description: The DefaultPersistenceDelegate is a concrete implementation of the abstract PersistenceDelegate class and is the delegate used by default for classes about which no information is available.

Class Summary.name: Encoder
Class Summary.description: An Encoder is a class which can be used to create files or streams that encode the state of a collection of JavaBeans in terms of their public APIs.

Class Summary.name: EventHandler
Class Summary.description: The EventHandler class provides support for dynamically generating event listeners whose methods execute a simple statement involving an incoming event object and a target object.

Class Summary.name: EventSetDescriptor
Class Summary.description: An EventSetDescriptor describes a group of events that a given Java bean fires.

Class Summary.name: Expression
Class Summary.description: An Expression object represents a primitive expression in which a single method is applied to a target and a set of arguments to return a result - as in "a.getFoo()".

Class Summary.name: FeatureDescriptor
Class Summary.description: The FeatureDescriptor class is the common baseclass for PropertyDescriptor, EventSetDescriptor, and MethodDescriptor, etc.

Class Summary.name: IndexedPropertyChangeEvent
Class Summary.description: An "IndexedPropertyChange" event gets delivered whenever a component that conforms to the JavaBeans specification (a "bean") changes a bound indexed property.

Class Summary.name: IndexedPropertyDescriptor
Class Summary.description: An IndexedPropertyDescriptor describes a property that acts like an array and has an indexed read and/or indexed write method to access specific elements of the array.

Class Summary.name: Introspector
Class Summary.description: The Introspector class provides a standard way for tools to learn about the properties, events, and methods supported by a target Java Bean.

Class Summary.name: MethodDescriptor
Class Summary.description: A MethodDescriptor describes a particular method that a Java Bean supports for external access from other components.

Class Summary.name: ParameterDescriptor
Class Summary.description: The ParameterDescriptor class allows bean implementors to provide additional information on each of their parameters, beyond the low level type information provided by the java.lang.reflect.Method class.

Class Summary.name: PersistenceDelegate
Class Summary.description: The PersistenceDelegate class takes the responsibility for expressing the state of an instance of a given class in terms of the methods in the class's public API.

Class Summary.name: PropertyChangeEvent
Class Summary.description: A "PropertyChange" event gets delivered whenever a bean changes a "bound" or "constrained" property.

Class Summary.name: PropertyChangeListenerProxy
Class Summary.description: A class which extends the EventListenerProxy specifically for adding a PropertyChangeListener with a "bound" property.

Class Summary.name: PropertyChangeSupport
Class Summary.description: This is a utility class that can be used by beans that support bound properties.

Class Summary.name: PropertyDescriptor
Class Summary.description: A PropertyDescriptor describes one property that a Java Bean exports via a pair of accessor methods.

Class Summary.name: PropertyEditorManager
Class Summary.description: The PropertyEditorManager can be used to locate a property editor for any given type name.

Class Summary.name: PropertyEditorSupport
Class Summary.description: This is a support class to help build property editors.

Class Summary.name: SimpleBeanInfo
Class Summary.description: This is a support class to make it easier for people to provide BeanInfo classes.

Class Summary.name: Statement
Class Summary.description: A Statement object represents a primitive statement in which a single method is applied to a target and a set of arguments - as in "a.setFoo(b)".

Class Summary.name: VetoableChangeListenerProxy
Class Summary.description: A class which extends the EventListenerProxy specifically for adding a VetoableChangeListener with a "constrained" property.

Class Summary.name: VetoableChangeSupport
Class Summary.description: This is a utility class that can be used by beans that support constrained properties.

Class Summary.name: XMLDecoder
Class Summary.description: The XMLDecoder class is used to read XML documents created using the XMLEncoder and is used just like the ObjectInputStream.

Class Summary.name: XMLEncoder
Class Summary.description: The XMLEncoder class is a complementary alternative to the ObjectOutputStream and can used to generate a textual representation of a JavaBean in the same way that the ObjectOutputStream can be used to create binary representation of Serializable objects.

Exception Summary.name: IntrospectionException
Exception Summary.description: Thrown when an exception happens during Introspection.

Exception Summary.name: PropertyVetoException
Exception Summary.description: A PropertyVetoException is thrown when a proposed change to a property represents an unacceptable value.

Annotation Types Summary.name: ConstructorProperties
Annotation Types Summary.description: An annotation on a constructor that shows how the parameters of that constructor correspond to the constructed object's getter methods.

Annotation Types Summary.name: Transient
Annotation Types Summary.description: Indicates that an attribute called "transient" should be declared with the given value when the Introspector constructs a PropertyDescriptor or EventSetDescriptor classes associated with the annotated code element.

name: java.beans.beancontext
description: Provides classes and interfaces relating to bean context.

Interface Summary.name: BeanContext
Interface Summary.description: The BeanContext acts a logical hierarchical container for JavaBeans.

Interface Summary.name: BeanContextChild
Interface Summary.description: JavaBeans wishing to be nested within, and obtain a reference to their execution environment, or context, as defined by the BeanContext sub-interface shall implement this interface.

Interface Summary.name: BeanContextChildComponentProxy
Interface Summary.description: This interface is implemented by BeanContextChildren that have an AWT Component associated with them.

Interface Summary.name: BeanContextContainerProxy
Interface Summary.description: This interface is implemented by BeanContexts' that have an AWT Container associated with them.

Interface Summary.name: BeanContextMembershipListener
Interface Summary.description: Compliant BeanContexts fire events on this interface when the state of the membership of the BeanContext changes.

Interface Summary.name: BeanContextProxy
Interface Summary.description: This interface is implemented by a JavaBean that does not directly have a BeanContext(Child) associated with it (via implementing that interface or a subinterface thereof), but has a public BeanContext(Child) delegated from it.

Interface Summary.name: BeanContextServiceProvider
Interface Summary.description: One of the primary functions of a BeanContext is to act a as rendezvous between JavaBeans, and BeanContextServiceProviders.

Interface Summary.name: BeanContextServiceProviderBeanInfo
Interface Summary.description: A BeanContextServiceProvider implementor who wishes to provide explicit information about the services their bean may provide shall implement a BeanInfo class that implements this BeanInfo subinterface and provides explicit information about the methods, properties, events, etc, of their services.

Interface Summary.name: BeanContextServiceRevokedListener
Interface Summary.description: The listener interface for receiving BeanContextServiceRevokedEvent objects.

Interface Summary.name: BeanContextServices
Interface Summary.description: The BeanContextServices interface provides a mechanism for a BeanContext to expose generic "services" to the BeanContextChild objects within.

Interface Summary.name: BeanContextServicesListener
Interface Summary.description: The listener interface for receiving BeanContextServiceAvailableEvent objects.

Class Summary.name: BeanContextChildSupport
Class Summary.description: This is a general support class to provide support for implementing the BeanContextChild protocol.

Class Summary.name: BeanContextEvent
Class Summary.description: BeanContextEvent is the abstract root event class for all events emitted from, and pertaining to the semantics of, a BeanContext.

Class Summary.name: BeanContextMembershipEvent
Class Summary.description: A BeanContextMembershipEvent encapsulates the list of children added to, or removed from, the membership of a particular BeanContext.

Class Summary.name: BeanContextServiceAvailableEvent
Class Summary.description: This event type is used by the BeanContextServicesListener in order to identify the service being registered.

Class Summary.name: BeanContextServiceRevokedEvent
Class Summary.description: This event type is used by the BeanContextServiceRevokedListener in order to identify the service being revoked.

Class Summary.name: BeanContextServicesSupport
Class Summary.description: This helper class provides a utility implementation of the java.beans.beancontext.BeanContextServices interface.

Class Summary.name: BeanContextServicesSupport.BCSSServiceProvider
Class Summary.description: subclasses may subclass this nested class to add behaviors for each BeanContextServicesProvider.

Class Summary.name: BeanContextSupport
Class Summary.description: This helper class provides a utility implementation of the java.beans.beancontext.BeanContext interface.

Class Summary.name: BeanContextSupport.BCSIterator
Class Summary.description: protected final subclass that encapsulates an iterator but implements a noop remove() method.

name: java.io
description: Provides for system input and output through data streams, serialization and the file system.

Interface Summary.name: Closeable
Interface Summary.description: A Closeable is a source or destination of data that can be closed.

Interface Summary.name: DataInput
Interface Summary.description: The DataInput interface provides for reading bytes from a binary stream and reconstructing from them data in any of the Java primitive types.

Interface Summary.name: DataOutput
Interface Summary.description: The DataOutput interface provides for converting data from any of the Java primitive types to a series of bytes and writing these bytes to a binary stream.

Interface Summary.name: Externalizable
Interface Summary.description: Only the identity of the class of an Externalizable instance is written in the serialization stream and it is the responsibility of the class to save and restore the contents of its instances.

Interface Summary.name: FileFilter
Interface Summary.description: A filter for abstract pathnames.

Interface Summary.name: FilenameFilter
Interface Summary.description: Instances of classes that implement this interface are used to filter filenames.

Interface Summary.name: Flushable
Interface Summary.description: A Flushable is a destination of data that can be flushed.

Interface Summary.name: ObjectInput
Interface Summary.description: ObjectInput extends the DataInput interface to include the reading of objects.

Interface Summary.name: ObjectInputValidation
Interface Summary.description: Callback interface to allow validation of objects within a graph.

Interface Summary.name: ObjectOutput

name: java.rmi
description: Provides the RMI package.

Exception Summary.name: ServerException

name: java.util.concurrent
description: Utility classes commonly useful in concurrent programming.

Interface Summary.name: BlockingDeque

Interface Summary.name: BlockingQueue
Interface Summary.description: A Queue that additionally supports operations that wait for the queue to become non-empty when retrieving an element, and wait for space to become available in the queue when storing an element.

Interface Summary.name: Callable
Interface Summary.description: A task that returns a result and may throw an exception.

Interface Summary.name: CompletableFuture.AsynchronousCompletionTask
Interface Summary.description: A marker interface identifying asynchronous tasks produced by async methods.

Interface Summary.name: CompletionService
Interface Summary.description: A service that decouples the production of new asynchronous tasks from the consumption of the results of completed tasks.

Interface Summary.name: CompletionStage
Interface Summary.description: A stage of a possibly asynchronous computation, that performs an action or computes a value when another CompletionStage completes.

Interface Summary.name: ConcurrentMap
Interface Summary.description: A Map providing thread safety and atomicity guarantees.

Interface Summary.name: ConcurrentNavigableMap
Interface Summary.description: A ConcurrentMap supporting NavigableMap operations, and recursively so for its navigable sub-maps.

Interface Summary.description: A handler for tasks that cannot be executed by a ThreadPoolExecutor.

Interface Summary.name: RunnableFuture
Interface Summary.description: A Future that is Runnable.

Interface Summary.description: A ScheduledFuture that is Runnable.

Interface Summary.name: ScheduledExecutorService
Interface Summary.description: An ExecutorService that can schedule commands to run after a given delay, or to execute periodically.

Interface Summary.name: ScheduledFuture
Interface Summary.description: A delayed result-bearing action that can be cancelled.

Interface Summary.name: ThreadFactory
Interface Summary.description: An object that creates new threads on demand.

Interface Summary.name: TransferQueue
Interface Summary.description: A BlockingQueue in which producers may wait for consumers to receive elements.
