name: javax.print
description: Provides the principal classes and interfaces for the JavaTM Print Service API.

Interface Summary.name: AttributeException
Interface Summary.description: Interface AttributeException is a mixin interface which a subclass of PrintException can implement to report an error condition involving one or more printing attributes that a particular Print Service instance does not support.

Interface Summary.name: CancelablePrintJob
Interface Summary.description: This interface is used by a printing application to cancel a print job.

Interface Summary.name: Doc
Interface Summary.description: Interface Doc specifies the interface for an object that supplies one piece of print data for a Print Job.

Interface Summary.name: DocPrintJob
Interface Summary.description: This interface represents a print job that can print a specified document with a set of job attributes.

Interface Summary.name: FlavorException
Interface Summary.description: Interface FlavorException is a mixin interface which a subclass of PrintException can implement to report an error condition involving a doc flavor or flavors (class DocFlavor).

Interface Summary.name: MultiDoc
Interface Summary.description: Interface MultiDoc specifies the interface for an object that supplies more than one piece of print data for a Print Job.

Interface Summary.name: MultiDocPrintJob
Interface Summary.description: Obtained from a MultiDocPrintService, a MultiDocPrintJob can print a specified collection of documents as a single print job with a set of job attributes.

Interface Summary.name: MultiDocPrintService
Interface Summary.description: Interface MultiPrintService is the factory for a MultiDocPrintJob.

Interface Summary.name: PrintService
Interface Summary.description: Interface PrintService is the factory for a DocPrintJob.

Interface Summary.name: URIException
Interface Summary.description: Interface URIException is a mixin interface which a subclass of PrintException can implement to report an error condition involving a URI address.

Class Summary.name: DocFlavor
Class Summary.description: Class DocFlavor encapsulates an object that specifies the format in which print data is supplied to a DocPrintJob.

Class Summary.name: DocFlavor.BYTE_ARRAY
Class Summary.description: Class DocFlavor.BYTE_ARRAY provides predefined static constant DocFlavor objects for example doc flavors using a byte array (byte[]) as the print data representation class.

Class Summary.name: DocFlavor.CHAR_ARRAY
Class Summary.description: Class DocFlavor.CHAR_ARRAY provides predefined static constant DocFlavor objects for example doc flavors using a character array (char[]) as the print data representation class.

Class Summary.name: DocFlavor.INPUT_STREAM
Class Summary.description: Class DocFlavor.INPUT_STREAM provides predefined static constant DocFlavor objects for example doc flavors using a byte stream (java.io.InputStream) as the print data representation class.

Class Summary.name: DocFlavor.READER
Class Summary.description: Class DocFlavor.READER provides predefined static constant DocFlavor objects for example doc flavors using a character stream (java.io.Reader) as the print data representation class.

Class Summary.name: DocFlavor.SERVICE_FORMATTED
Class Summary.description: Class DocFlavor.SERVICE_FORMATTED provides predefined static constant DocFlavor objects for example doc flavors for service formatted print data.

Class Summary.name: DocFlavor.STRING
Class Summary.description: Class DocFlavor.STRING provides predefined static constant DocFlavor objects for example doc flavors using a string (java.lang.String) as the print data representation class.

Class Summary.name: DocFlavor.URL
Class Summary.description: Class DocFlavor.URL provides predefined static constant DocFlavor objects.

Class Summary.name: PrintServiceLookup
Class Summary.description: Implementations of this class provide lookup services for print services (typically equivalent to printers) of a particular type.

Class Summary.name: ServiceUI
Class Summary.description: This class is a collection of UI convenience methods which provide a graphical user dialog for browsing print services looked up through the Java Print Service API.

Class Summary.name: ServiceUIFactory
Class Summary.description: Services may optionally provide UIs which allow different styles of interaction in different roles.

Class Summary.name: SimpleDoc
Class Summary.description: This class is an implementation of interface Doc that can be used in many common printing requests.

Class Summary.name: StreamPrintService
Class Summary.description: This class extends PrintService and represents a print service that prints data in different formats to a client-provided output stream.

Class Summary.name: StreamPrintServiceFactory
Class Summary.description: A StreamPrintServiceFactory is the factory for StreamPrintService instances, which can print to an output stream in a particular document format described as a mime type.

Exception Summary.name: PrintException
Exception Summary.description: Class PrintException encapsulates a printing-related error condition that occurred while using a Print Service instance.

name: javax.print.attribute
description: Provides classes and interfaces that describe the types of JavaTM Print Service attributes and how they can be collected into attribute sets.

Interface Summary.name: Attribute
Interface Summary.description: Interface Attribute is the base interface implemented by any and every printing attribute class to indicate that the class represents a printing attribute.

Interface Summary.name: AttributeSet
Interface Summary.description: Interface AttributeSet specifies the interface for a set of printing attributes.

Interface Summary.name: DocAttribute
Interface Summary.description: Interface DocAttribute is a tagging interface which a printing attribute class implements to indicate the attribute denotes a setting for a doc.

Interface Summary.name: DocAttributeSet
Interface Summary.description: Interface DocAttributeSet specifies the interface for a set of doc attributes, i.e.

Interface Summary.name: PrintJobAttribute
Interface Summary.description: PrintJobAttribute is a tagging interface which a printing attribute class implements to indicate the attribute describes the status of a Print Job or some other characteristic of a Print Job.

Interface Summary.name: PrintJobAttributeSet
Interface Summary.description: Interface PrintJobAttributeSet specifies the interface for a set of print job attributes, i.e.

Interface Summary.name: PrintRequestAttribute
Interface Summary.description: Interface PrintRequestAttribute is a tagging interface which a printing attribute class implements to indicate the attribute denotes a requested setting for a print job.

Interface Summary.name: PrintRequestAttributeSet
Interface Summary.description: Interface PrintRequestAttributeSet specifies the interface for a set of print request attributes, i.e.

Interface Summary.name: PrintServiceAttribute
Interface Summary.description: Interface PrintServiceAttribute is a tagging interface which a printing attribute class implements to indicate the attribute describes the status of a Print Service or some other characteristic of a Print Service.

Interface Summary.name: PrintServiceAttributeSet
Interface Summary.description: Interface PrintServiceAttributeSet specifies the interface for a set of print job attributes, i.e.

Interface Summary.name: SupportedValuesAttribute
Interface Summary.description: Interface SupportedValuesAttribute is a tagging interface which a printing attribute class implements to indicate the attribute describes the supported values for another attribute.

Class Summary.name: AttributeSetUtilities
Class Summary.description: Class AttributeSetUtilities provides static methods for manipulating AttributeSets.

Class Summary.name: DateTimeSyntax
Class Summary.description: Class DateTimeSyntax is an abstract base class providing the common implementation of all attributes whose value is a date and time.

Class Summary.name: EnumSyntax
Class Summary.description: Class EnumSyntax is an abstract base class providing the common implementation of all "type safe enumeration" objects.

Class Summary.name: HashAttributeSet
Class Summary.description: Class HashAttributeSet provides an AttributeSet implementation with characteristics of a hash map.

Class Summary.name: HashDocAttributeSet
Class Summary.description: Class HashDocAttributeSet provides an attribute set which inherits its implementation from class HashAttributeSet and enforces the semantic restrictions of interface DocAttributeSet.

Class Summary.name: HashPrintJobAttributeSet
Class Summary.description: Class HashPrintJobAttributeSet provides an attribute set which inherits its implementation from class HashAttributeSet and enforces the semantic restrictions of interface PrintJobAttributeSet.

Class Summary.name: HashPrintRequestAttributeSet
Class Summary.description: Class HashPrintRequestAttributeSet inherits its implementation from class HashAttributeSet and enforces the semantic restrictions of interface PrintRequestAttributeSet.

Class Summary.name: HashPrintServiceAttributeSet
Class Summary.description: Class HashPrintServiceAttributeSet provides an attribute set which inherits its implementation from class HashAttributeSet and enforces the semantic restrictions of interface PrintServiceAttributeSet.

Class Summary.name: IntegerSyntax
Class Summary.description: Class IntegerSyntax is an abstract base class providing the common implementation of all attributes with integer values.

Class Summary.name: ResolutionSyntax
Class Summary.description: Class ResolutionSyntax is an abstract base class providing the common implementation of all attributes denoting a printer resolution.

Class Summary.name: SetOfIntegerSyntax
Class Summary.description: Class SetOfIntegerSyntax is an abstract base class providing the common implementation of all attributes whose value is a set of nonnegative integers.

Class Summary.name: Size2DSyntax
Class Summary.description: Class Size2DSyntax is an abstract base class providing the common implementation of all attributes denoting a size in two dimensions.

Class Summary.name: TextSyntax
Class Summary.description: Class TextSyntax is an abstract base class providing the common implementation of all attributes whose value is a string.

Class Summary.name: URISyntax
Class Summary.description: Class URISyntax is an abstract base class providing the common implementation of all attributes whose value is a Uniform Resource Identifier (URI).

Exception Summary.name: UnmodifiableSetException
Exception Summary.description: Thrown to indicate that the requested operation cannot be performed because the set is unmodifiable.

name: javax.print.attribute.standard
description: Package javax.print.attribute.standard contains classes for specific printing attributes.

Class Summary.name: Chromaticity
Class Summary.description: Class Chromaticity is a printing attribute class, an enumeration, that specifies monochrome or color printing.

Class Summary.name: ColorSupported
Class Summary.description: Class ColorSupported is a printing attribute class, an enumeration, that identifies whether the device is capable of any type of color printing at all, including highlight color as well as full process color.

Class Summary.name: Compression
Class Summary.description: Class Compression is a printing attribute class, an enumeration, that specifies how print data is compressed.

Class Summary.name: Copies
Class Summary.description: Class Copies is an integer valued printing attribute class that specifies the number of copies to be printed.

Class Summary.name: CopiesSupported
Class Summary.description: Class CopiesSupported is a printing attribute class, a set of integers, that gives the supported values for a Copies attribute.

Class Summary.name: DateTimeAtCompleted
Class Summary.description: Class DateTimeAtCompleted is a printing attribute class, a date-time attribute, that indicates the date and time at which the Print Job completed (or was canceled or aborted).

Class Summary.name: DateTimeAtCreation
Class Summary.description: Class DateTimeAtCreation is a printing attribute class, a date-time attribute, that indicates the date and time at which the Print Job was created.

Class Summary.name: DateTimeAtProcessing
Class Summary.description: Class DateTimeAtProcessing is a printing attribute class, a date-time attribute, that indicates the date and time at which the Print Job first began processing.

Class Summary.name: Destination
Class Summary.description: Class Destination is a printing attribute class, a URI, that is used to indicate an alternate destination for the spooled printer formatted data.

Class Summary.name: DialogTypeSelection
Class Summary.description: Class DialogTypeSelection is a printing attribute class, an enumeration, that indicates the user dialog type to be used for specifying printing options.

Class Summary.name: DocumentName
Class Summary.description: Class DocumentName is a printing attribute class, a text attribute, that specifies the name of a document.

Class Summary.name: Fidelity
Class Summary.description: Class Fidelity is a printing attribute class, an enumeration, that indicates whether total fidelity to client supplied print request attributes is required.

Class Summary.name: Finishings
Class Summary.description: Class Finishings is a printing attribute class, an enumeration, that identifies whether the printer applies a finishing operation of some kind of binding to each copy of each printed document in the job.

Class Summary.name: JobHoldUntil
Class Summary.description: Class JobHoldUntil is a printing attribute class, a date-time attribute, that specifies the exact date and time at which the job must become a candidate for printing.

Class Summary.name: JobImpressions
Class Summary.description: Class JobImpressions is an integer valued printing attribute class that specifies the total size in number of impressions of the document(s) being submitted.

Class Summary.name: JobImpressionsCompleted
Class Summary.description: Class JobImpressionsCompleted is an integer valued printing attribute class that specifies the number of impressions completed for the job so far.

Class Summary.name: JobImpressionsSupported
Class Summary.description: Class JobImpressionsSupported is a printing attribute class, a set of integers, that gives the supported values for a JobImpressions attribute.

Class Summary.name: JobKOctets
Class Summary.description: Class JobKOctets is an integer valued printing attribute class that specifies the total size of the document(s) in K octets, i.e., in units of 1024 octets requested to be processed in the job.

Class Summary.name: JobKOctetsProcessed
Class Summary.description: Class JobKOctetsProcessed is an integer valued printing attribute class that specifies the total number of print data octets processed so far in K octets, i.e., in units of 1024 octets.

Class Summary.name: JobKOctetsSupported
Class Summary.description: Class JobKOctetsSupported is a printing attribute class, a set of integers, that gives the supported values for a JobKOctets attribute.

Class Summary.name: JobMediaSheets
Class Summary.description: Class JobMediaSheets is an integer valued printing attribute class that specifies the total number of media sheets to be produced for this job.

Class Summary.name: JobMediaSheetsCompleted
Class Summary.description: Class JobMediaSheetsCompleted is an integer valued printing attribute class that specifies the number of media sheets which have completed marking and stacking for the entire job so far, whether those sheets have been processed on one side or on both.

Class Summary.name: JobMediaSheetsSupported
Class Summary.description: Class JobMediaSheetsSupported is a printing attribute class, a set of integers, that gives the supported values for a JobMediaSheets attribute.

Class Summary.name: JobMessageFromOperator
Class Summary.description: Class JobMessageFromOperator is a printing attribute class, a text attribute, that provides a message from an operator, system administrator, or "intelligent" process to indicate to the end user the reasons for modification or other management action taken on a job.

Class Summary.name: JobName
Class Summary.description: Class JobName is a printing attribute class, a text attribute, that specifies the name of a print job.

Class Summary.name: JobOriginatingUserName
Class Summary.description: Class JobOriginatingUserName is a printing attribute class, a text attribute, that contains the name of the end user that submitted the print job.

Class Summary.name: JobPriority
Class Summary.description: Class JobPriority is an integer valued printing attribute class that specifies a print job's priority.

Class Summary.name: JobPrioritySupported
Class Summary.description: Class JobPrioritySupported is an integer valued printing attribute class that specifies whether a Print Service instance supports the JobPriority attribute and the number of different job priority levels supported.

Class Summary.name: JobSheets
Class Summary.description: Class JobSheets is a printing attribute class, an enumeration, that determines which job start and end sheets, if any, must be printed with a job.

Class Summary.name: JobState
Class Summary.description: JobState is a printing attribute class, an enumeration, that identifies the current state of a print job.

Class Summary.name: JobStateReason
Class Summary.description: Class JobStateReason is a printing attribute class, an enumeration, that provides additional information about the job's current state, i.e., information that augments the value of the job's JobState attribute.

Class Summary.name: JobStateReasons
Class Summary.description: Class JobStateReasons is a printing attribute class, a set of enumeration values, that provides additional information about the job's current state, i.e., information that augments the value of the job's JobState attribute.

Class Summary.name: Media
Class Summary.description: Class Media is a printing attribute class that specifies the medium on which to print.

Class Summary.name: MediaName
Class Summary.description: Class MediaName is a subclass of Media, a printing attribute class (an enumeration) that specifies the media for a print job as a name.

Class Summary.name: MediaPrintableArea
Class Summary.description: Class MediaPrintableArea is a printing attribute used to distinguish the printable and non-printable areas of media.

Class Summary.name: MediaSize
Class Summary.description: Class MediaSize is a two-dimensional size valued printing attribute class that indicates the dimensions of the medium in a portrait orientation, with the X dimension running along the bottom edge and the Y dimension running along the left edge.

Class Summary.name: MediaSize.Engineering
Class Summary.description: Class MediaSize.Engineering includes MediaSize values for engineering media.

Class Summary.name: MediaSize.ISO
Class Summary.description: Class MediaSize.ISO includes MediaSize values for ISO media.

Class Summary.name: MediaSize.JIS
Class Summary.description: Class MediaSize.JIS includes MediaSize values for JIS (Japanese) media.

Class Summary.name: MediaSize.NA
Class Summary.description: Class MediaSize.NA includes MediaSize values for North American media.

Class Summary.name: MediaSize.Other
Class Summary.description: Class MediaSize.Other includes MediaSize values for miscellaneous media.

Class Summary.name: MediaSizeName
Class Summary.description: Class MediaSizeName is a subclass of Media.

Class Summary.name: MediaTray
Class Summary.description: Class MediaTray is a subclass of Media.

Class Summary.name: MultipleDocumentHandling
Class Summary.description: Class MultipleDocumentHandling is a printing attribute class, an enumeration, that controls finishing operations and the placement of one or more print-stream pages into impressions and onto media sheets.

Class Summary.name: NumberOfDocuments
Class Summary.description: Class NumberOfDocuments is an integer valued printing attribute that indicates the number of individual docs the printer has accepted for this job, regardless of whether the docs' print data has reached the printer or not.

Class Summary.name: NumberOfInterveningJobs
Class Summary.description: Class NumberOfInterveningJobs is an integer valued printing attribute that indicates the number of jobs that are ahead of this job in the relative chronological order of expected time to complete (i.e., the current scheduled order).

Class Summary.name: NumberUp
Class Summary.description: Class NumberUp is an integer valued printing attribute class that specifies the number of print-stream pages to impose upon a single side of an instance of a selected medium.

Class Summary.name: NumberUpSupported
Class Summary.description: Class NumberUpSupported is a printing attribute class, a set of integers, that gives the supported values for a NumberUp attribute.

Class Summary.name: OrientationRequested
Class Summary.description: Class OrientationRequested is a printing attribute class, an enumeration, that indicates the desired orientation for printed print-stream pages; it does not describe the orientation of the client-supplied print-stream pages.

Class Summary.name: OutputDeviceAssigned
Class Summary.description: Class OutputDeviceAssigned is a printing attribute class, a text attribute, that identifies the output device to which the service has assigned this job.

Class Summary.name: PageRanges
Class Summary.description: Class PageRanges is a printing attribute class, a set of integers, that identifies the range(s) of print-stream pages that the Printer object uses for each copy of each document which are to be printed.

Class Summary.name: PagesPerMinute
Class Summary.description: Class PagesPerMinute is an integer valued printing attribute that indicates the nominal number of pages per minute to the nearest whole number which may be generated by this printer (e.g., simplex, black-and-white).

Class Summary.name: PagesPerMinuteColor
Class Summary.description: Class PagesPerMinuteColor is an integer valued printing attribute that indicates the nominal number of pages per minute to the nearest whole number which may be generated by this printer when printing color (e.g., simplex, color).

Class Summary.name: PDLOverrideSupported
Class Summary.description: Class PDLOverrideSupported is a printing attribute class, an enumeration, that expresses the printer's ability to attempt to override processing instructions embedded in documents' print data with processing instructions specified as attributes outside the print data.

Class Summary.name: PresentationDirection
Class Summary.description: Class PresentationDirection is a printing attribute class, an enumeration, that is used in conjunction with the NumberUp attribute to indicate the layout of multiple print-stream pages to impose upon a single side of an instance of a selected medium.

Class Summary.name: PrinterInfo
Class Summary.description: Class PrinterInfo is a printing attribute class, a text attribute, that provides descriptive information about a printer.

Class Summary.name: PrinterIsAcceptingJobs
Class Summary.description: Class PrinterIsAcceptingJobs is a printing attribute class, an enumeration, that indicates whether the printer is currently able to accept jobs.

Class Summary.name: PrinterLocation
Class Summary.description: Class PrinterLocation is a printing attribute class, a text attribute, that identifies the location of the device.

Class Summary.name: PrinterMakeAndModel
Class Summary.description: Class PrinterMakeAndModel is a printing attribute class, a text attribute, that the make and model of the printer.

Class Summary.name: PrinterMessageFromOperator
Class Summary.description: Class PrinterMessageFromOperator is a printing attribute class, a text attribute, that provides a message from an operator, system administrator, or "intelligent" process to indicate to the end user information about or status of the printer, such as why it is unavailable or when it is expected to be available.

Class Summary.name: PrinterMoreInfo
Class Summary.description: Class PrinterMoreInfo is a printing attribute class, a URI, that is used to obtain more information about this specific printer.

Class Summary.name: PrinterMoreInfoManufacturer
Class Summary.description: Class PrinterMoreInfoManufacturer is a printing attribute class, a URI, that is used to obtain more information about this type of device.

Class Summary.name: PrinterName
Class Summary.description: Class PrinterName is a printing attribute class, a text attribute, that specifies the name of a printer.

Class Summary.name: PrinterResolution
Class Summary.description: Class PrinterResolution is a printing attribute class that specifies an exact resolution supported by a printer or to be used for a print job.

Class Summary.name: PrinterState
Class Summary.description: Class PrinterState is a printing attribute class, an enumeration, that identifies the current state of a printer.

Class Summary.name: PrinterStateReason
Class Summary.description: Class PrinterStateReason is a printing attribute class, an enumeration, that provides additional information about the printer's current state, i.e., information that augments the value of the printer's PrinterState attribute.

Class Summary.name: PrinterStateReasons
Class Summary.description: Class PrinterStateReasons is a printing attribute class, a set of enumeration values, that provides additional information about the printer's current state, i.e., information that augments the value of the printer's PrinterState attribute.

Class Summary.name: PrinterURI
Class Summary.description: Class PrinterURI is a printing attribute class, a URI, that specifies the globally unique name of a printer.

Class Summary.name: PrintQuality
Class Summary.description: Class PrintQuality is a printing attribute class, an enumeration, that specifies the print quality that the printer uses for the job.

Class Summary.name: QueuedJobCount
Class Summary.description: Class QueuedJobCount is an integer valued printing attribute that indicates the number of jobs in the printer whose JobState is either PENDING, PENDING_HELD, PROCESSING, or PROCESSING_STOPPED.

Class Summary.name: ReferenceUriSchemesSupported
Class Summary.description: Class ReferenceUriSchemesSupported is a printing attribute class an enumeration, that indicates a "URI scheme," such as "http:" or "ftp:", that a printer can use to retrieve print data stored at a URI location.

Class Summary.name: RequestingUserName
Class Summary.description: Class RequestingUserName is a printing attribute class, a text attribute, that specifies the name of the end user that submitted the print job.

Class Summary.name: Severity
Class Summary.description: Class Severity is a printing attribute class, an enumeration, that denotes the severity of a PrinterStateReason attribute.

Class Summary.name: SheetCollate
Class Summary.description: Class SheetCollate is a printing attribute class, an enumeration, that specifies whether or not the media sheets of each copy of each printed document in a job are to be in sequence, when multiple copies of the document are specified by the Copies attribute.

Class Summary.name: Sides
Class Summary.description: Class Sides is a printing attribute class, an enumeration, that specifies how print-stream pages are to be imposed upon the sides of an instance of a selected medium, i.e., an impression.

name: javax.print.event
description: Package javax.print.event contains event classes and listener interfaces.

Class Summary.name: CompiledScript

Class Summary.name: SimpleBindings

Class Summary.name: SimpleScriptContext

name: javax.security.auth

Interface Summary.name: Refreshable
Interface Summary.description: Objects such as credentials may optionally implement this interface to provide the capability to refresh itself.

Class Summary.name: AuthPermission
Class Summary.description: This class is for authentication permissions.

Class Summary.name: Policy
Class Summary.description: Deprecated as of JDK version 1.4 -- Replaced by java.security.Policy.

Class Summary.name: PrivateCredentialPermission
Class Summary.description: This class is used to protect access to private Credentials belonging to a particular Subject.

Class Summary.name: Subject

Exception Summary.name: DestroyFailedException

Exception Summary.name: RefreshFailedException

name: javax.security.auth.callback

Interface Summary.name: CallbackHandler

Class Summary.name: LanguageCallback

Class Summary.name: NameCallback

Class Summary.name: PasswordCallback

Class Summary.name: TextInputCallback
Class Summary.description: Underlying security services instantiate and pass a TextInputCallback to the handle method of a CallbackHandler to retrieve generic text information.

Class Summary.name: TextOutputCallback
Class Summary.description: Underlying security services instantiate and pass a TextOutputCallback to the handle method of a CallbackHandler to display information messages, warning messages and error messages.

Exception Summary.name: UnsupportedCallbackException

name: javax.sound.midi
description: Provides interfaces and classes for I/O, sequencing, and synthesis of MIDI (Musical Instrument Digital Interface) data.

Interface Summary.name: ControllerEventListener
Interface Summary.description: The ControllerEventListener interface should be implemented by classes whose instances need to be notified when a Sequencer has processed a requested type of MIDI control-change event.

Interface Summary.name: MetaEventListener
Interface Summary.description: The MetaEventListener interface should be implemented by classes whose instances need to be notified when a Sequencer has processed a MetaMessage.

Interface Summary.name: MidiChannel
Interface Summary.description: A MidiChannel object represents a single MIDI channel.

Interface Summary.name: MidiDevice
Interface Summary.description: MidiDevice is the base interface for all MIDI devices.

Interface Summary.name: MidiDeviceReceiver
Interface Summary.description: MidiDeviceReceiver is a Receiver which represents a MIDI input connector of a MidiDevice (see MidiDevice.getReceiver()).

Interface Summary.name: MidiDeviceTransmitter
Interface Summary.description: MidiDeviceTransmitter is a Transmitter which represents a MIDI input connector of a MidiDevice (see MidiDevice.getTransmitter()).

Interface Summary.name: Receiver
Interface Summary.description: A Receiver receives MidiEvent objects and typically does something useful in response, such as interpreting them to generate sound or raw MIDI output.

Interface Summary.name: Sequencer
Interface Summary.description: A hardware or software device that plays back a MIDI sequence is known as a sequencer.

Interface Summary.name: Soundbank
Interface Summary.description: A Soundbank contains a set of Instruments that can be loaded into a Synthesizer.

Interface Summary.name: Synthesizer
Interface Summary.description: A Synthesizer generates sound.

Interface Summary.name: Transmitter
Interface Summary.description: A Transmitter sends MidiEvent objects to one or more Receivers.

Class Summary.name: Instrument
Class Summary.description: An instrument is a sound-synthesis algorithm with certain parameter settings, usually designed to emulate a specific real-world musical instrument or to achieve a specific sort of sound effect.

Class Summary.name: MetaMessage
Class Summary.description: A MetaMessage is a MidiMessage that is not meaningful to synthesizers, but that can be stored in a MIDI file and interpreted by a sequencer program.

Class Summary.name: MidiDevice.Info
Class Summary.description: A MidiDevice.Info object contains assorted data about a MidiDevice, including its name, the company who created it, and descriptive text.

Class Summary.name: MidiEvent
Class Summary.description: MIDI events contain a MIDI message and a corresponding time-stamp expressed in ticks, and can represent the MIDI event information stored in a MIDI file or a Sequence object.

Class Summary.name: MidiFileFormat
Class Summary.description: A MidiFileFormat object encapsulates a MIDI file's type, as well as its length and timing information.

Class Summary.name: MidiMessage
Class Summary.description: MidiMessage is the base class for MIDI messages.

Class Summary.name: MidiSystem
Class Summary.description: The MidiSystem class provides access to the installed MIDI system resources, including devices such as synthesizers, sequencers, and MIDI input and output ports.

Class Summary.name: Patch
Class Summary.description: A Patch object represents a location, on a MIDI synthesizer, into which a single instrument is stored (loaded).

Class Summary.name: Sequence
Class Summary.description: A Sequence is a data structure containing musical information (often an entire song or composition) that can be played back by a Sequencer object.

Class Summary.name: Sequencer.SyncMode
Class Summary.description: A SyncMode object represents one of the ways in which a MIDI sequencer's notion of time can be synchronized with a master or slave device.

Class Summary.name: ShortMessage
Class Summary.description: A ShortMessage contains a MIDI message that has at most two data bytes following its status byte.

Class Summary.name: SoundbankResource
Class Summary.description: A SoundbankResource represents any audio resource stored in a Soundbank.

Class Summary.name: SysexMessage
Class Summary.description: A SysexMessage object represents a MIDI system exclusive message.

Class Summary.name: Track
Class Summary.description: A MIDI track is an independent stream of MIDI events (time-stamped MIDI data) that can be stored along with other tracks in a standard MIDI file.

Class Summary.name: VoiceStatus
Class Summary.description: A VoiceStatus object contains information about the current status of one of the voices produced by a Synthesizer.

Exception Summary.name: InvalidMidiDataException
Exception Summary.description: An InvalidMidiDataException indicates that inappropriate MIDI data was encountered.

Exception Summary.name: MidiUnavailableException

Class Summary.name: SoundbankReader

Exception Summary.name: ACTIVITY_COMPLETED
Exception Summary.description: The ACTIVITY_COMPLETED system exception may be raised on any method for which Activity context is accessed.

Exception Summary.description: The ACTIVITY_REQUIRED system exception may be raised on any method for which an Activity context is required.

Exception Summary.name: BAD_CONTEXT
Exception Summary.description: Exception thrown when an operation is invoked by a client but the passed context does not contain the context values required by the operation.

Exception Summary.name: BAD_INV_ORDER
Exception Summary.description: This exception indicates that the caller has invoked operations in the wrong order.

Exception Summary.name: BAD_OPERATION
Exception Summary.description: Exception thrown when an object reference denotes an existing object, but that the object does not support the operation that was invoked.

Exception Summary.name: BAD_PARAM
Exception Summary.description: Exception thrown when a parameter passed to a call is out of range or otherwise considered illegal.

Exception Summary.name: BAD_QOS
Exception Summary.description: The BAD_QOS exception is raised whenever an object cannot support the quality of service required by an invocation parameter that has a quality of service semantics associated with it.

Exception Summary.name: BAD_TYPECODE
Exception Summary.description: Exception thrown when the ORB has encountered a malformed type code (for example, a type code with an invalid TCKind value).

Exception Summary.name: Bounds
Exception Summary.description: A user exception thrown when a parameter is not within the legal bounds for the object that a method is trying to access.

Exception Summary.name: CODESET_INCOMPATIBLE
Exception Summary.description: This exception is raised whenever meaningful communication is not possible between client and server native code sets.

Exception Summary.name: COMM_FAILURE
Exception Summary.description: This exception is raised if communication is lost while an operation is in progress, after the request was sent by the client, but before the reply from the server has been returned to the client.

Exception Summary.name: DATA_CONVERSION
Exception Summary.description: This exception is raised if an ORB cannot convert the representation of data as marshaled into its native representation or vice-versa.

Exception Summary.name: FREE_MEM
Exception Summary.description: Exception thrown when the ORB failed in an attempt to free dynamic memory, for example because of heap corruption or memory segments being locked.

Exception Summary.name: IMP_LIMIT
Exception Summary.description: This exception indicates that an implementation limit was exceeded in the ORB run time.

Exception Summary.name: INITIALIZE
Exception Summary.description: Exception thrown when an ORB has encountered a failure during its initialization, such as failure to acquire networking resources or detecting a configuration error.

Exception Summary.name: INTERNAL
Exception Summary.description: This exception indicates an internal failure in an ORB, for example, if an ORB has detected corruption of its internal data structures.

Exception Summary.name: INTF_REPOS
Exception Summary.description: Exception raised when an ORB cannot reach the interface repository, or some other failure relating to the interface repository is detected.

Exception Summary.name: INV_FLAG
Exception Summary.description: Exception thrown when an invalid flag was passed to an operation (for example, when creating a DII request).

Exception Summary.name: INV_IDENT
Exception Summary.description: This exception indicates that an IDL identifier is syntactically invalid.

Exception Summary.name: INV_OBJREF
Exception Summary.description: This exception indicates that an object reference is internally malformed.

Exception Summary.name: INV_POLICY
Exception Summary.description: Standard exception thrown when an invocation cannot be made because of an incompatibility between Policy overrides that apply to the particular invocation.

Exception Summary.name: INVALID_ACTIVITY
Exception Summary.description: The INVALID_ACTIVITY system exception may be raised on the Activity or Transaction services' resume methods if a transaction or Activity is resumed in a context different to that from which it was suspended.

Exception Summary.name: INVALID_TRANSACTION
Exception Summary.description: Exception thrown when the request carried an invalid transaction context.

Exception Summary.name: MARSHAL
Exception Summary.description: A request or reply from the network is structurally invalid.

Exception Summary.name: NO_IMPLEMENT
Exception Summary.description: This exception indicates that even though the operation that was invoked exists (it has an IDL definition), no implementation for that operation exists.

Exception Summary.name: NO_MEMORY
Exception Summary.description: Exception thrown when the ORB run time has run out of memory.

Exception Summary.name: NO_PERMISSION
Exception Summary.description: Exception thrown when an invocation failed because the caller has insufficient privileges.

Exception Summary.name: NO_RESOURCES
Exception Summary.description: Exception thrown when the ORB has encountered some general resource limitation.

Exception Summary.name: NO_RESPONSE
Exception Summary.description: This exception is raised if a client attempts to retrieve the result of a deferred synchronous call, but the response for the request is not yet available.

Exception Summary.name: OBJ_ADAPTER
Exception Summary.description: This exception typically indicates an administrative mismatch, for example, a server may have made an attempt to register itself with an implementation repository under a name that is already in use, or is unknown to the repository.

Exception Summary.name: OBJECT_NOT_EXIST
Exception Summary.description: Exception raised whenever an invocation on a deleted object was performed.

Exception Summary.name: PERSIST_STORE
Exception Summary.description: This exception indicates a persistent storage failure, for example, failure to establish a database connection or corruption of a database.

Exception Summary.name: PolicyError
Exception Summary.description: A user exception thrown when a policy error occurs.

Exception Summary.name: REBIND
Exception Summary.description: REBIND is raised when the current effective RebindPolicy, has a value of NO_REBIND or NO_RECONNECT and an invocation on a bound object reference results in a LocateReply message with status OBJECT_FORWARD or a Reply message with status LOCATION_FORWARD.

Exception Summary.name: SystemException
Exception Summary.description: The root class for all CORBA standard exceptions.

Exception Summary.name: TIMEOUT
Exception Summary.description: TIMEOUT is raised when no delivery has been made and the specified time-to-live period has been exceeded.

Exception Summary.name: TRANSACTION_MODE
Exception Summary.description: The CORBA TRANSACTION_MODE exception is thrown by the client ORB if it detects a mismatch between the InvocationPolicy in the IOR and the chosen invocation path (i.e, direct or routed invocation).

Exception Summary.name: TRANSACTION_REQUIRED
Exception Summary.description: Exception indicates that the request carried a null transaction context, but an active transaction is required.

Exception Summary.name: TRANSACTION_ROLLEDBACK
Exception Summary.description: Exception thrown when the transaction associated with the request has already been rolled back or marked to roll back.

Exception Summary.name: TRANSACTION_UNAVAILABLE
Exception Summary.description: The CORBA TRANSACTION_UNAVAILABLE exception is thrown by the ORB when it cannot process a transaction service context because its connection to the Transaction Service has been abnormally terminated.

Exception Summary.name: TRANSIENT
Exception Summary.description: Exception thrown when the ORB attempted to reach an object and failed.

Exception Summary.name: UNKNOWN
Exception Summary.description: This exception is raised if an operation implementation throws a non-CORBA exception (such as an exception specific to the implementation's programming language), or if an operation raises a user exception that does not appear in the operation's raises expression.

Exception Summary.name: UserException
Exception Summary.description: The root class for CORBA IDL-defined user exceptions.

Exception Summary.name: WrongTransaction
Exception Summary.description: The CORBA WrongTransaction user-defined exception.

name: org.w3c.dom
description: Provides the interfaces for the Document Object Model (DOM).

Interface Summary.name: Attr
Interface Summary.description: The Attr interface represents an attribute in an Element object.

Interface Summary.name: CDATASection
Interface Summary.description: CDATA sections are used to escape blocks of text containing characters that would otherwise be regarded as markup.

Interface Summary.name: CharacterData
Interface Summary.description: The CharacterData interface extends Node with a set of attributes and methods for accessing character data in the DOM.

Interface Summary.name: Comment
Interface Summary.description: This interface inherits from CharacterData and represents the content of a comment, i.e., all the characters between the starting ' <!--' and ending '-->'.

Interface Summary.name: Document
Interface Summary.description: The Document interface represents the entire HTML or XML document.

Interface Summary.name: DocumentFragment
Interface Summary.description: DocumentFragment is a "lightweight" or "minimal" Document object.

Interface Summary.name: DocumentType
Interface Summary.description: Each Document has a doctype attribute whose value is either null or a DocumentType object.

Interface Summary.name: DOMConfiguration
Interface Summary.description: The DOMConfiguration interface represents the configuration of a document and maintains a table of recognized parameters.

Interface Summary.name: DOMError
Interface Summary.description: DOMError is an interface that describes an error.

Interface Summary.name: DOMErrorHandler
Interface Summary.description: DOMErrorHandler is a callback interface that the DOM implementation can call when reporting errors that happens while processing XML data, or when doing some other processing (e.g.

Interface Summary.name: DOMImplementation
Interface Summary.description: The DOMImplementation interface provides a number of methods for performing operations that are independent of any particular instance of the document object model.

Interface Summary.name: DOMImplementationList
Interface Summary.description: The DOMImplementationList interface provides the abstraction of an ordered collection of DOM implementations, without defining or constraining how this collection is implemented.

Interface Summary.name: DOMImplementationSource
Interface Summary.description: This interface permits a DOM implementer to supply one or more implementations, based upon requested features and versions, as specified in DOM Features.

Interface Summary.name: DOMLocator
Interface Summary.description: DOMLocator is an interface that describes a location (e.g.

Interface Summary.name: DOMStringList
Interface Summary.description: The DOMStringList interface provides the abstraction of an ordered collection of DOMString values, without defining or constraining how this collection is implemented.

Interface Summary.name: Element
Interface Summary.description: The Element interface represents an element in an HTML or XML document.

Interface Summary.name: Entity
Interface Summary.description: This interface represents a known entity, either parsed or unparsed, in an XML document.

Interface Summary.name: EntityReference
Interface Summary.description: EntityReference nodes may be used to represent an entity reference in the tree.

Interface Summary.name: NamedNodeMap
Interface Summary.description: Objects implementing the NamedNodeMap interface are used to represent collections of nodes that can be accessed by name.

Interface Summary.name: NameList
Interface Summary.description: The NameList interface provides the abstraction of an ordered collection of parallel pairs of name and namespace values (which could be null values), without defining or constraining how this collection is implemented.

Interface Summary.name: Node
Interface Summary.description: The Node interface is the primary datatype for the entire Document Object Model.

Interface Summary.name: NodeList
Interface Summary.description: The NodeList interface provides the abstraction of an ordered collection of nodes, without defining or constraining how this collection is implemented.

Interface Summary.name: Notation
Interface Summary.description: This interface represents a notation declared in the DTD.

Interface Summary.name: ProcessingInstruction
Interface Summary.description: The ProcessingInstruction interface represents a "processing instruction", used in XML as a way to keep processor-specific information in the text of the document.

Interface Summary.name: Text
Interface Summary.description: The Text interface inherits from CharacterData and represents the textual content (termed character data in XML) of an Element or Attr.

Interface Summary.name: TypeInfo
Interface Summary.description: The TypeInfo interface represents a type referenced from Element or Attr nodes, specified in the schemas associated with the document.

Interface Summary.name: UserDataHandler
Interface Summary.description: When associating an object to a key on a node using Node.setUserData() the application can provide a handler that gets called when the node the object is associated to is being cloned, imported, or renamed.

Exception Summary.name: DOMException
Exception Summary.description: DOM operations only raise exceptions in "exceptional" circumstances, i.e., when an operation is impossible to perform (either for logical reasons, because data is lost, or because the implementation has become unstable).

Class Summary.name: DOMImplementationRegistry
Class Summary.description: A factory that enables applications to obtain instances of DOMImplementation.

Interface Summary.name: DocumentEvent
Interface Summary.description: The DocumentEvent interface provides a mechanism by which the user can create an Event of a type supported by the implementation.

Interface Summary.name: Event
Interface Summary.description: The Event interface is used to provide contextual information about an event to the handler processing the event.

Interface Summary.name: EventListener
Interface Summary.description: The EventListener interface is the primary method for handling events.

Interface Summary.name: EventTarget
Interface Summary.description: The EventTarget interface is implemented by all Nodes in an implementation which supports the DOM Event Model.

Interface Summary.name: MouseEvent
Interface Summary.description: The MouseEvent interface provides specific contextual information associated with Mouse events.

Interface Summary.name: MutationEvent
Interface Summary.description: The MutationEvent interface provides specific contextual information associated with Mutation events.

Interface Summary.name: UIEvent
Interface Summary.description: The UIEvent interface provides specific contextual information associated with User Interface events.

Exception Summary.name: EventException
Exception Summary.description: Event operations may throw an EventException as specified in their method descriptions.

Interface Summary.name: DOMImplementationLS
Interface Summary.description: DOMImplementationLS contains the factory methods for creating Load and Save objects.

Interface Summary.name: LSInput
Interface Summary.description: This interface represents an input source for data.

Interface Summary.name: LSLoadEvent
Interface Summary.description: This interface represents a load event object that signals the completion of a document load.

Interface Summary.name: LSOutput
Interface Summary.description: This interface represents an output destination for data.

Interface Summary.name: LSParser
Interface Summary.description: An interface to an object that is able to build, or augment, a DOM tree from various input sources.

Interface Summary.name: LSParserFilter
Interface Summary.description: LSParserFilters provide applications the ability to examine nodes as they are being constructed while parsing.

Interface Summary.name: LSProgressEvent
Interface Summary.description: This interface represents a progress event object that notifies the application about progress as a document is parsed.

Interface Summary.name: LSResourceResolver
Interface Summary.description: LSResourceResolver provides a way for applications to redirect references to external resources.

Interface Summary.name: LSSerializer
Interface Summary.description: A LSSerializer provides an API for serializing (writing) a DOM document out into XML.

Interface Summary.name: LSSerializerFilter
Interface Summary.description: LSSerializerFilters provide applications the ability to examine nodes as they are being serialized and decide what nodes should be serialized or not.

Exception Summary.name: LSException
Exception Summary.description: Parser or write operations may throw an LSException if the processing is stopped.

Interface Summary.name: AbstractView
Interface Summary.description: A base interface that all views shall derive from.

Interface Summary.name: DocumentView
Interface Summary.description: The DocumentView interface is implemented by Document objects in DOM implementations supporting DOM Views.
